1
00:00:00,467 --> 00:00:05,439
[Bonjour Bakery]

2
00:00:05,439 --> 00:00:07,641
[50 Minutes Before Day 3 Begins]

3
00:00:07,641 --> 00:00:09,109
Bonjour.

4
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:23,924
[Slowly Writing Down Today's Menu]

5
00:00:23,924 --> 00:00:26,092
Brûlée, brûlée.

6
00:00:27,628 --> 00:00:30,130
Camellia Tart.

7
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:32,366
Good morning.

8
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:34,201
Will you stop by later?

9
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:35,502
No?

10
00:00:36,937 --> 00:00:38,405
Have a nice day.

11
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:41,374
She smiled and said nothing.

12
00:00:46,580 --> 00:00:48,382
[Bonjour Green Barley Tart]

13
00:00:48,382 --> 00:00:50,817
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake]

14
00:00:50,817 --> 00:00:53,086
[Bonjour Camellia Tart]

15
00:00:53,086 --> 00:00:54,988
[Bonjour Crème Brûlée]

16
00:00:54,988 --> 00:00:56,857
[Bonjour Financier]

17
00:00:56,857 --> 00:01:00,394
[Bonjour Madeleines]
[Citron, <i>Bokbunja</i>, Green Barley]

18
00:01:00,394 --> 00:01:03,330
[Bonjour Chestnut Pumpkin Babka]

19
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:07,801
[30 Minutes Before Opening]

20
00:01:07,801 --> 00:01:09,937
[Someone Stops]

21
00:01:09,937 --> 00:01:13,473
[In Front Of The Bakery]

22
00:01:13,473 --> 00:01:17,043
[Looking Around]

23
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:26,786
No one's here.

24
00:01:30,724 --> 00:01:33,260
Anyone around?

25
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,728
[Are You]

26
00:01:34,728 --> 00:01:37,130
[Open Today?]

27
00:01:37,130 --> 00:01:38,732
- It's...
- We also got radish kimchi.

28
00:01:38,732 --> 00:01:41,902
It's made with winter radish,
and it's so sweet.

29
00:01:41,902 --> 00:01:43,070
- Salted oysters.
- Yes.

30
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,538
- It looks so good.
- They're from Tongyeong.

31
00:01:44,538 --> 00:01:46,006
- They taste so good.
- When did you get them?

32
00:01:46,006 --> 00:01:48,976
[Everyone Is Busy]
We tried a sample and had to get them.

33
00:01:48,976 --> 00:01:50,410
I love them.

34
00:01:50,410 --> 00:01:54,801
[But Why Did He Walk In?]

35
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:58,318
[We Are Closed]

36
00:01:58,318 --> 00:01:59,519
[Just Now]

37
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:03,056
[The Wind Turned The Sign Around]

38
00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:06,326
[He Had No Idea They Weren't Open]

39
00:02:06,326 --> 00:02:07,794
No one's here.

40
00:02:09,196 --> 00:02:12,299
[Maybe They're Not Open Yet]

41
00:02:12,899 --> 00:02:16,069
[I'll Come Again Next Time]

42
00:02:18,038 --> 00:02:21,308
[Is Someone Here?]

43
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:25,645
Why am I nervous?

44
00:02:28,281 --> 00:02:30,183
I'm nervous for some reason.

45
00:02:30,183 --> 00:02:32,386
Me too.

46
00:02:32,386 --> 00:02:34,321
You've got your hat pulled on tight.

47
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:36,523
- Yes.
- Good, it won't budge.

48
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:39,292
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

49
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:47,467
[We Are Open]

50
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:51,304
[11:00 A.M.]
[Open For Business]

51
00:02:53,407 --> 00:02:54,574
- Hello.
- Hello.

52
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:56,009
- Hello.
- Hello.

53
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,344
- Welcome.
- Hello.

54
00:03:02,315 --> 00:03:04,985
- Hello.
- Hello.

55
00:03:04,985 --> 00:03:07,287
- Let's have a seat here.
- Please have a seat.

56
00:03:09,289 --> 00:03:11,024
- Is that Mrs. Kwak?
- What?

57
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:13,560
- Is that Mrs. Kwak?
- Yes, it is.

58
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,062
It's good to see her here.

59
00:03:15,062 --> 00:03:16,930
[Nice To See Our Neighbors]

60
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,900
Hello, welcome.

61
00:03:21,468 --> 00:03:23,303
Please come this way.

62
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:25,839
- I'll bring you a chair.
- Hello.

63
00:03:25,839 --> 00:03:27,307
[Recognizing Hee Ae]
Welcome.

64
00:03:27,307 --> 00:03:29,876
- Yes, nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

65
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:32,312
Please wait just a moment.

66
00:03:32,312 --> 00:03:34,848
[Brings An Extra Chair]

67
00:03:34,848 --> 00:03:36,183
Thank you.

68
00:03:36,183 --> 00:03:38,418
It's okay. I'll do it.

69
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:42,723
[Table For 3 Is Ready]

70
00:03:42,723 --> 00:03:44,391
Please wait just one moment.

71
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:45,726
- Would you like to sit here?
- Have a seat.

72
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:47,560
No, you sit there.

73
00:03:48,528 --> 00:03:50,464
- This is great.
- She's so pretty.

74
00:03:50,464 --> 00:03:51,898
[In-Laws With Their Daughter-In-Law]

75
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,700
Sorry, but can I check your ID?

76
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,169
One person needs to be over 65 years old.

77
00:03:56,169 --> 00:03:57,738
- Show him yours.
- Okay.

78
00:03:57,738 --> 00:03:59,639
Here, I'm younger than this.

79
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:01,775
My dad wrote down the wrong birthday.

80
00:04:01,775 --> 00:04:04,444
You look so young for your age.

81
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:07,714
- My goodness.
- You look around 42 years old.

82
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:09,282
One year older than me.

83
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:13,086
It's on me today.

84
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,687
[Daughter-In-Law's Treat]

85
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,890
- This...
- What's that?

86
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,761
It says it captures green barley fields.

87
00:04:20,761 --> 00:04:22,262
What is it made of?

88
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,830
[Carefully Choosing The Menu]

89
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:25,799
- Almond...
- Turn the page.

90
00:04:25,799 --> 00:04:27,000
[Suddenly Turns The Page]

91
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,735
- Let's eat something simple.
- Sweet Potato Cake.

92
00:04:28,735 --> 00:04:30,871
Let's get this Sweet Potato Cake.

93
00:04:30,871 --> 00:04:32,339
- Citron madeleine.
- Just pick the one at the front.

94
00:04:32,339 --> 00:04:33,940
Hold on, let's see the menu.

95
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:36,009
Let's take our time.

96
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:37,544
Please wait a while.

97
00:04:37,544 --> 00:04:39,079
<i>Bokbunja.</i>

98
00:04:40,013 --> 00:04:42,215
Have you decided on your drinks?

99
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:44,951
[The Manager Steps In]
It'll be faster if you order drinks first.

100
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,787
Two hot café lattes, please.

101
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:49,356
Two café lattes.

102
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:51,792
And one iced Americano, please.

103
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:52,926
All right.

104
00:04:52,926 --> 00:04:54,628
- Thank you.
- No problem.

105
00:04:54,628 --> 00:04:57,764
Two hot café lattes and one iced Americano.

106
00:04:57,764 --> 00:04:59,466
Coming right up.

107
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:02,769
[Order Received]

108
00:05:11,912 --> 00:05:15,982
[Skillfully Prepares Two Drinks]

109
00:05:22,756 --> 00:05:26,993
[Flawless Workflow With Zero Wasted Steps]

110
00:05:39,072 --> 00:05:42,509
[Even Latte Art?]

111
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:47,781
[Proud Of Himself]
Can you take a look at this, Hee Ae?

112
00:05:47,781 --> 00:05:51,151
[Even The Heart Came Out Great]
I've improved a lot, right?

113
00:05:51,151 --> 00:05:52,852
You're amazing.

114
00:05:53,987 --> 00:05:55,455
Cha Seung Won isn't here.

115
00:05:55,455 --> 00:05:57,190
- He must be cooking.
- What?

116
00:05:57,190 --> 00:06:00,093
He must be cooking in the kitchen.

117
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:02,996
You said you had something to tell him.

118
00:06:02,996 --> 00:06:04,564
Not really.

119
00:06:04,564 --> 00:06:05,966
It's nothing.

120
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:09,836
When he was filming <i>Three Meals a Day</i>,
he would eat <i>Jjajangmyeon</i>.

121
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:11,504
- There he is. Hello.
- Hello.

122
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:13,773
- Hello.
- Hello.

123
00:06:13,773 --> 00:06:16,676
[Appears At The Perfect Moment]

124
00:06:16,676 --> 00:06:17,911
He came at the perfect time.

125
00:06:17,911 --> 00:06:19,980
Hello, welcome.

126
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:22,048
- You come to Gochang often.
- Yes.

127
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:24,184
[Fangirl Mode Activated]

128
00:06:24,184 --> 00:06:25,418
You ordered that one.

129
00:06:25,418 --> 00:06:26,486
- Yes.
- I...

130
00:06:26,486 --> 00:06:28,355
Nice to meet you.

131
00:06:28,355 --> 00:06:30,123
[Well-Known To Gochang Locals
Through Three Meals A Day]

132
00:06:30,123 --> 00:06:31,424
Excuse me.

133
00:06:31,424 --> 00:06:32,893
[Coffee Is Served]
Thank you.

134
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,361
- Who ordered the iced Americano?
- Me.

135
00:06:36,596 --> 00:06:39,099
Yours has a heart, but not mine.

136
00:06:39,099 --> 00:06:40,533
The truth is,

137
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:42,435
I failed while making yours.

138
00:06:42,435 --> 00:06:44,037
- Thank you.
- I wanted to make a heart.

139
00:06:44,037 --> 00:06:47,240
- How is it?
- Thanks for buying us some time.

140
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,309
I'll help you guys out.

141
00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:52,445
[He'll Buy Some Time
If It's The Manager's Request]

142
00:06:52,445 --> 00:06:56,016
- Where do you buy the bread?
- We make them here, ma'am.

143
00:06:56,016 --> 00:06:57,684
- Where do we pay?
- We would like to buy some.

144
00:06:57,684 --> 00:07:00,120
- You can pay for it right there.
- All right.

145
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,021
But...

146
00:07:01,021 --> 00:07:03,423
[The Manager Can Slow Down Thanks To Him]

147
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:08,261
I love how soft this is.

148
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:10,630
[Dessert Is Also Served]
That was quick. Thank you.

149
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,098
Thank you.

150
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:17,070
- Let's dig in.
- I want to take a picture.

151
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:21,041
[Frozen Until She Takes A Photo]

152
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,942
[Set Free!]
Let's try this.

153
00:07:23,543 --> 00:07:25,045
It's like matcha.

154
00:07:25,045 --> 00:07:27,280
[Starts With The Green Barley Madeleine]

155
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,582
- They added a lot of green barley.
- Really?

156
00:07:29,582 --> 00:07:31,551
I can taste it.

157
00:07:32,686 --> 00:07:35,922
- Yes, the bread.
- I should get some to go.

158
00:07:35,922 --> 00:07:37,624
- I'd like some to go.
- You can come take a look.

159
00:07:38,558 --> 00:07:40,527
[Pay At The Counter For Takeout]
Let us know if you want it to go.

160
00:07:40,527 --> 00:07:42,495
They're on display over there.

161
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:46,967
- I'll take three citron madeleines.
- Three citron madeleines.

162
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,501
And three green barley madeleines.

163
00:07:48,501 --> 00:07:50,270
- Three of each.
- Five financiers.

164
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,671
Five.

165
00:07:51,671 --> 00:07:54,808
Three, three, and five.

166
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,242
And two babkas.

167
00:07:56,242 --> 00:07:57,377
Two babkas.

168
00:07:57,377 --> 00:07:59,679
Just two babkas.

169
00:08:01,414 --> 00:08:04,651
[We Should Get Some To Go]

170
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:07,821
- We can order to go here?
- Yes.

171
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:10,356
- Let's get some to take home.
- Okay.

172
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:13,793
This and the bread...

173
00:08:13,793 --> 00:08:16,262
[Crowded With People]
Should we put them together? Thank you.

174
00:08:16,262 --> 00:08:18,331
We'll take three babkas.

175
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,232
Per person.

176
00:08:19,232 --> 00:08:21,001
- That many?
- Yes.

177
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:23,103
Three financiers.

178
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:24,504
Two citron madeleines.

179
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,773
- Two <i>bokbunja</i>.
- Please wait a moment.

180
00:08:26,773 --> 00:08:28,141
Two financiers.

181
00:08:28,141 --> 00:08:29,909
[Order Rush]
Three citron madeleines.

182
00:08:29,909 --> 00:08:31,578
And three <i>bokbunja</i>.

183
00:08:31,578 --> 00:08:33,680
- One.
- All right.

184
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:36,182
[Must Remain Calm]

185
00:08:36,883 --> 00:08:39,152
[Hands Moving Faster]

186
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:42,722
[As The Orders Pour In]

187
00:08:45,392 --> 00:08:46,726
You ordered three, right?

188
00:08:46,726 --> 00:08:48,895
- Here you go.
- Please insert your card.

189
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:50,363
Which...

190
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:52,766
- Which three did you want?
- This one and this one.

191
00:08:52,766 --> 00:08:54,801
This one and this one? Okay.

192
00:08:55,935 --> 00:08:59,672
[It's Chaotic,
But They're Taking It One Step At A Time]

193
00:08:59,672 --> 00:09:01,741
Here are all your orders.

194
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:03,410
- They're ready.
- Thank you.

195
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:06,413
[Nearly Finished To-Go Orders]
Here you go. You can pay here.

196
00:09:06,413 --> 00:09:08,481
- Bye.
- Thank you.

197
00:09:08,481 --> 00:09:10,950
Would you like a receipt? No?

198
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:12,518
Thank you.

199
00:09:18,191 --> 00:09:20,326
Here you go, sir.

200
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:22,462
- Your to-go order is ready.
- Okay.

201
00:09:22,462 --> 00:09:26,166
[Packing Up The Very Last Order]

202
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:30,203
[And Heading Straight
To Clear The Empty Tables]

203
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:37,644
[Stack The Plates To Clear Them At Once]

204
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:40,546
[Carrying Two Cups In One Hand Like A Pro]

205
00:09:44,451 --> 00:09:47,520
[Cleaning Up By Himself At Lightning Speed]

206
00:09:48,621 --> 00:09:51,958
[Meanwhile, The Kitchen Team]

207
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,726
Okay, babka.

208
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:54,627
Babka.

209
00:09:54,627 --> 00:09:56,663
[Babka]

210
00:09:56,663 --> 00:09:59,732
[A Name That Rolls Off Your Tongue
For Some Reason]

211
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,503
[It Means "Little Grandmother"
In Slavic Languages]

212
00:10:03,503 --> 00:10:06,106
[A Eastern European Holiday Bread]

213
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:07,474
[Famous For Its Fun]

214
00:10:07,474 --> 00:10:09,542
[Intricately Braided Shape]

215
00:10:11,211 --> 00:10:12,645
[Bonjour Bakery's Secret Kick Is]

216
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:15,281
[The Sweet Chestnut Pumpkin Filling!]

217
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:21,454
[Yesterday Afternoon]

218
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:25,158
[Make The Chestnut Pumpkin Filling
The Day Before]

219
00:10:31,931 --> 00:10:37,804
[Ki Taek Peeled The Pumpkins
Without Straightening His Back Even Once]

220
00:10:40,173 --> 00:10:42,575
[Mix Together Sweet Pumpkin]

221
00:10:42,575 --> 00:10:44,811
[Chestnut Pumpkin Powder]

222
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:46,880
[Butter]

223
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:50,283
[And White Chocolate]

224
00:10:57,223 --> 00:11:03,062
[Flatten The Filling Out Evenly
With A Rolling Pin]

225
00:11:03,062 --> 00:11:05,031
- It looks great, right?
- Yes.

226
00:11:05,031 --> 00:11:10,036
[After Chilling The Flattened Filling
In The Refrigerator For A Day]

227
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:15,675
[Spread A Thick Layer
Between The Babka Dough]

228
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:19,078
You know, this ruler is...

229
00:11:19,078 --> 00:11:20,480
[A Ruler In The Kitchen?]
The 4.5 mark is unclear.

230
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,515
This is 4.5, right?

231
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:26,886
[Taking The Exact Measurements With A Ruler]

232
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:27,987
[Time For]

233
00:11:27,987 --> 00:11:30,389
[Precise, Meticulously Measured Cutting]

234
00:11:31,224 --> 00:11:32,292
[Length Is 18Cm]

235
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:34,861
[Width Is 4.5Cm]

236
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:49,642
[While Dividing It Into Three Equal Parts]

237
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:54,046
[Confused]

238
00:11:54,948 --> 00:11:57,750
Why does this feel different from last time?

239
00:11:57,750 --> 00:12:00,286
Why?

240
00:12:01,254 --> 00:12:02,555
Oh, no.

241
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:03,856
This is bad.

242
00:12:03,856 --> 00:12:05,358
[Tremble]

243
00:12:05,358 --> 00:12:06,759
This won't work.

244
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:11,297
[When Practicing]

245
00:12:12,265 --> 00:12:14,934
[The Dough Separated Cleanly
Along The Cut Lines]

246
00:12:14,934 --> 00:12:16,002
This is...

247
00:12:16,002 --> 00:12:17,603
[But Today]

248
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:20,740
[It's Stuck To The Surface]

249
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:21,975
It melted, right?

250
00:12:21,975 --> 00:12:23,977
We can't use this.

251
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:26,913
[Encountered A Problem In The Process]
This is going to tear apart.

252
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:30,350
I can't use it because it's sticky.

253
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:35,455
The temperature here is different
from where we had the lessons.

254
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:37,623
[Stretch]

255
00:12:39,025 --> 00:12:40,593
[Floppy]

256
00:12:43,896 --> 00:12:46,332
[Current Temperature Is 20 Celsius]

257
00:12:46,332 --> 00:12:48,935
Is it because it's too hot in here?

258
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:51,838
- In the kitchen?
- It's a warm day today.

259
00:12:51,838 --> 00:12:53,973
- The weather affects it a lot.
- That's right.

260
00:12:53,973 --> 00:12:57,143
[Floppy Dough Affected By Hot Weather]
Bread is very sensitive to the weather.

261
00:12:57,143 --> 00:12:59,746
Then let's freeze it.

262
00:12:59,746 --> 00:13:01,881
This is really bad.

263
00:13:01,881 --> 00:13:06,018
[Carefully Peels It Off]

264
00:13:08,421 --> 00:13:12,592
[Extreme Measures]
[Straight To The Freezer]

265
00:13:12,592 --> 00:13:14,160
[Bonjour Bakery]

266
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,897
[Will They Be Able
To Bring The Dough Back To Life?]

267
00:13:18,498 --> 00:13:22,268
[The Dough Just Came Out Of The Freezer]

268
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:25,037
[Press]

269
00:13:25,838 --> 00:13:27,873
[Is It Okay?]

270
00:13:30,276 --> 00:13:31,444
It's working.

271
00:13:31,444 --> 00:13:34,447
[It's Cutting Without Sticking!]

272
00:13:37,617 --> 00:13:40,052
[Divide Into Three Strands]

273
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:48,461
[Interlacing The Three Strands Of Dough]

274
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:50,663
[Like A Classic Hair Braid]

275
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:54,901
[The Secret To Its Twisted Shape]

276
00:13:54,901 --> 00:13:56,469
[Girl-Dad Cha Seung Won's]

277
00:13:56,469 --> 00:13:59,772
[Masterful Braiding Skills]

278
00:14:03,743 --> 00:14:04,811
It looks nice.

279
00:14:04,811 --> 00:14:06,045
[Roll It Into A Circle]

280
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:08,381
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

281
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:13,786
[Put The Dough In The Shaped Tins]

282
00:14:13,786 --> 00:14:16,756
[Once The Dough Has Taken Its Shape]

283
00:14:17,724 --> 00:14:21,093
[It's Time To Bake Them!]

284
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:26,799
[Bake It At 150 Degrees
So The Inside Stays Moist]

285
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,535
[Soaking Up That Gentle Heat]

286
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:35,007
[The Babka Blooms Like A Soft, Fluffy Flower]

287
00:14:40,747 --> 00:14:42,215
- Be careful.
- I will.

288
00:14:42,215 --> 00:14:43,683
[It's Hot]

289
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:55,828
[Bonjour Chestnut Pumpkin Babka]

290
00:14:56,596 --> 00:15:00,666
Chestnut pumpkin babuka bread!

291
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:01,567
- Is that good?
- Bonjour.

292
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:06,406
Bonjour Baboka bread.

293
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:08,307
It's delicious.

294
00:15:08,307 --> 00:15:10,243
Welcome.

295
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:11,310
How many people?

296
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:12,278
- Four.
- Four?

297
00:15:12,278 --> 00:15:14,280
I have to check your ID.

298
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,949
- Our IDs?
- Yes, you have to be over 65.

299
00:15:16,949 --> 00:15:18,317
I just need one person's.

300
00:15:18,317 --> 00:15:21,287
He says he just needs to check one person.

301
00:15:21,287 --> 00:15:23,856
- No need to take yours out.
- Right.

302
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:25,625
[Verification Complete]
Thank you.

303
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:27,026
I'm going to...

304
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:30,329
I'll bring the menu,
so please wait just a moment.

305
00:15:30,329 --> 00:15:34,333
- Give us your best stuff.
- Okay, I will.

306
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:38,304
[Finishes Cleaning
While On His Way To Get The Menu]

307
00:15:39,071 --> 00:15:42,341
We serve bread,
so here are wet towels for your hands.

308
00:15:42,341 --> 00:15:44,811
The front page shows the coffee menu,
followed by desserts.

309
00:15:44,811 --> 00:15:46,779
Please take your time.

310
00:15:47,580 --> 00:15:51,884
[Cleans The Tables
While Waiting For Them To Order]

311
00:15:57,256 --> 00:15:58,591
- Aren't you tired?
- Sorry?

312
00:15:58,591 --> 00:15:59,792
Aren't you tired?

313
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:02,395
I'm okay.

314
00:16:02,395 --> 00:16:04,197
Is it open for business now?

315
00:16:04,197 --> 00:16:06,899
- That's right.
- I see.

316
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:09,302
This used to be all gravel.

317
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:12,772
- It was filled with gravel.
- They renovated it.

318
00:16:12,772 --> 00:16:15,141
[Elders From The Village Next Door]

319
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:17,376
- Look at that junk.
- What?

320
00:16:17,376 --> 00:16:19,278
It's an old piece of junk.

321
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:21,714
They washed it.

322
00:16:21,714 --> 00:16:23,816
There's also a straw bag.

323
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:25,017
[It's A Vintage Piece]

324
00:16:25,017 --> 00:16:26,853
They hung a straw bag.

325
00:16:26,853 --> 00:16:28,955
[Once A Canvas Bag, Now A Straw Bag]
They decorated with lots of things.

326
00:16:28,955 --> 00:16:32,024
What's in this junk?

327
00:16:32,024 --> 00:16:34,126
There's a book as well.

328
00:16:34,694 --> 00:16:36,262
- Let's take a look.
- It's old.

329
00:16:36,262 --> 00:16:37,897
[Exploring The Bakery Excitedly]

330
00:16:37,897 --> 00:16:39,699
- It's all in English.
- I can't see a thing clearly.

331
00:16:39,699 --> 00:16:41,300
- I can't see it at all.
- It's in English.

332
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,435
- I can't see a thing clearly.
- I can't see it at all.

333
00:16:42,435 --> 00:16:44,237
- I can't see it at all.
- It's in English.

334
00:16:44,237 --> 00:16:45,471
I'm still young.

335
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:49,442
[While They're Busy Exploring The Bakery]

336
00:16:49,442 --> 00:16:52,445
[He Comes To Take Their Order]

337
00:16:52,445 --> 00:16:54,814
Let's order four of them.
We need one for each person.

338
00:16:54,814 --> 00:16:55,915
Just have three!

339
00:16:55,915 --> 00:16:57,817
- We're going to be too full.
- I'm hungry.

340
00:16:57,817 --> 00:16:59,185
I haven't eaten yet.

341
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:00,152
May I take your order?

342
00:17:00,152 --> 00:17:01,087
- Yes.
- Yes.

343
00:17:01,087 --> 00:17:02,488
<i>- Bokbunja.</i>
- Okay, <i>bokbunja</i>.

344
00:17:02,488 --> 00:17:03,422
This one is from Seonunsa.

345
00:17:03,422 --> 00:17:04,857
- Just one?
- Next.

346
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:05,992
- What?
- Citron.

347
00:17:05,992 --> 00:17:07,360
- Citron.
- Citron?

348
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,695
- One chestnut pumpkin.
- Okay.

349
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:12,298
- Green barley.
- Green barley.

350
00:17:12,298 --> 00:17:13,566
- Sweet Potato Cake.
- Sweet potato!

351
00:17:13,566 --> 00:17:14,800
- Yes, sweet potato.
- Sweet potato.

352
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,968
Those four.

353
00:17:15,968 --> 00:17:17,803
- That's actually five.
- Is it?

354
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:20,006
- That's too much.
- <i>Bokbunja</i>, citron...

355
00:17:20,006 --> 00:17:21,674
Just order it.

356
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:22,909
Just have two.

357
00:17:22,909 --> 00:17:25,044
[Grumpy Because Things Didn't Go His Way]
We'll divide it between us.

358
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,113
Would you like all five?
Should I cancel one?

359
00:17:27,113 --> 00:17:29,782
<i>Bokbunja</i> and citron are both madeleines.

360
00:17:29,782 --> 00:17:32,218
Which one should I cancel?

361
00:17:32,218 --> 00:17:33,219
- Four...
- Cancel the citron.

362
00:17:33,219 --> 00:17:34,754
- Citron?
- Cancel the citron.

363
00:17:34,754 --> 00:17:36,455
[Ended Up Ordering Four]
So that's <i>bokbunja</i>, chestnut pumpkin,

364
00:17:36,455 --> 00:17:38,591
Green Barley Madeleine,
and Sweet Potato Cake, one each.

365
00:17:38,591 --> 00:17:39,792
What about the drinks?

366
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:41,027
Coffee with milk.

367
00:17:41,027 --> 00:17:42,428
- With milk?
- Yes.

368
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:44,063
Do you want it sweetened?

369
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,131
Just a little bit.

370
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:46,399
- Sweetened one?
- A little bit.

371
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:48,100
I would like some soda.

372
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,202
- What?
- I would like a soda.

373
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:54,307
We don't have soda, but we have orangeade.

374
00:17:54,307 --> 00:17:57,710
[Satisfying Everyone]
It's made with orange, juice, and soda.

375
00:17:57,710 --> 00:17:59,278
[While Smoothly Wrapping Up The Order]
What do you think?

376
00:17:59,278 --> 00:18:01,013
Okay, one orangeade.

377
00:18:01,647 --> 00:18:03,883
- Thank you.
- Take care.

378
00:18:03,883 --> 00:18:04,884
Goodbye.

379
00:18:04,884 --> 00:18:07,520
Have a good day.

380
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:11,691
- You looked slightly fuller on screen.
- Yes.

381
00:18:11,691 --> 00:18:13,159
- I lost weight, right?
- Yes.

382
00:18:13,159 --> 00:18:15,294
Were you skinny, or did you lose weight?

383
00:18:15,294 --> 00:18:16,629
I lost it on purpose.

384
00:18:16,629 --> 00:18:18,264
- My goodness.
- You have nothing left to lose.

385
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:20,800
- I lost around 10kg.
- It seems like it.

386
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,135
Around 10kg or 11kg.

387
00:18:23,135 --> 00:18:25,504
Everyone tells me to gain weight.

388
00:18:26,372 --> 00:18:30,676
But I couldn't because
of my filming schedule.

389
00:18:30,676 --> 00:18:32,945
- I see.
- Your voice is...

390
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,080
- Yes?
- It sounds so nice.

391
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,815
- It's not just his voice.
- It seems unreal.

392
00:18:35,815 --> 00:18:36,949
Really?

393
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:39,552
- Seriously.
- Thank you.

394
00:18:39,552 --> 00:18:41,587
[Shuts The Door So No Wind Gets In]
He was always a nice guy.

395
00:18:41,587 --> 00:18:43,589
- It feels like a dream.
- My goodness.

396
00:18:43,589 --> 00:18:44,824
I feel awakened by your voice.

397
00:18:44,824 --> 00:18:46,659
[Adding Some Sweetness]
You had something.

398
00:18:46,659 --> 00:18:49,261
- He is so thoughtful.
- I've never seen

399
00:18:49,261 --> 00:18:52,832
such a handsome guy in Gochang.

400
00:18:52,832 --> 00:18:54,133
[It's Not Just Gochang]

401
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:57,103
[They're Rare Everywhere Else Too]

402
00:18:57,103 --> 00:18:58,704
[The Menus Are Ready]
Could you please help me, Hee Ae?

403
00:18:58,704 --> 00:19:01,807
- Yes.
- Could you just bring those three plates?

404
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:04,310
- Yes, I was about to.
- Okay.

405
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,212
You wanted it less sweetened, right?

406
00:19:06,212 --> 00:19:08,214
- Here are the rest.
- The sweet one for me.

407
00:19:08,214 --> 00:19:10,316
- The sweet one.
- Thank you.

408
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:14,220
You wanted soda, so here is your orangeade.

409
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:16,856
I'll bring the plates. Please wait a moment.

410
00:19:16,856 --> 00:19:17,857
[Once Drinks Are Served]
Thank you.

411
00:19:17,857 --> 00:19:22,995
[Desserts Come Right After]

412
00:19:23,863 --> 00:19:25,231
[4 Desserts Are Served]
These are the Sweet Potato Cake,

413
00:19:25,231 --> 00:19:28,167
Chestnut Pumpkin Babka, and the madeleine.

414
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:29,902
Here they are.

415
00:19:29,902 --> 00:19:31,137
[Stares At The Dessert]

416
00:19:31,137 --> 00:19:33,272
Ta-da!

417
00:19:33,973 --> 00:19:37,476
It's not one per person?

418
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:40,513
I thought we were each having one.

419
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,416
That's why I wanted three.

420
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:44,917
Are we supposed to share these?

421
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:46,585
Yes.

422
00:19:50,523 --> 00:19:52,191
Split into four.

423
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,259
[Splitting Them Equally]

424
00:19:53,259 --> 00:19:55,261
I'll split this one.

425
00:19:55,261 --> 00:19:56,662
Use your fork to cut it.

426
00:19:56,662 --> 00:19:58,497
[Trying His Best]

427
00:19:58,497 --> 00:20:00,199
My goodness.

428
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:04,269
Try all of them.

429
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:09,174
[He Considerately Pushes The Plates
Toward Them]

430
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:14,413
Thank you very much.

431
00:20:14,413 --> 00:20:16,649
- Thank you.
- You're very beautiful.

432
00:20:16,649 --> 00:20:18,484
Pardon me for saying this,

433
00:20:18,484 --> 00:20:19,819
but you're very stylish.

434
00:20:19,819 --> 00:20:20,886
- Thank you.
- Yes.

435
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:22,588
Thank you so much.

436
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:25,491
- Thank you.
- Can I get a handshake?

437
00:20:25,491 --> 00:20:27,693
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

438
00:20:27,693 --> 00:20:28,694
[Capturing The Joy Of This Moment]

439
00:20:28,694 --> 00:20:31,497
One, two, three.

440
00:20:31,497 --> 00:20:32,798
You're so pretty.

441
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:35,134
- Thank you.
- Yes.

442
00:20:35,134 --> 00:20:36,135
Take care.

443
00:20:36,135 --> 00:20:37,770
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

444
00:20:40,673 --> 00:20:42,274
[From The Morning]
<i>Hello, welcome.</i>

445
00:20:42,274 --> 00:20:44,543
[A Pleasant Buzz Continues]
<i>Hello, welcome.</i>

446
00:20:44,543 --> 00:20:46,612
[The Kitchen Team Joins To Help]
Two citron.

447
00:20:46,612 --> 00:20:48,314
- We have to refill this, Ki Taek.
- Okay.

448
00:20:48,314 --> 00:20:49,482
- Okay.
- All of these.

449
00:20:49,482 --> 00:20:50,382
All right.

450
00:20:50,382 --> 00:20:51,650
Hold on.

451
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:54,320
[3 Gentlemen Observe Them]

452
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,088
[Ko Hyeon Sang, Oh Pyo Geun, Ko Du Seong]

453
00:20:57,323 --> 00:20:58,657
- It's Kim Hee Ae.
- What?

454
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:00,359
Kim Hee Ae.

455
00:21:00,359 --> 00:21:02,027
- Where?
- Over there.

456
00:21:02,728 --> 00:21:04,830
- Is it her?
- Yes, she's there.

457
00:21:05,464 --> 00:21:06,365
[Their Eyes Only On Hee Ae]
Over there.

458
00:21:06,365 --> 00:21:08,334
[Stumbles]
My goodness.

459
00:21:08,334 --> 00:21:09,335
Oh, really?

460
00:21:09,335 --> 00:21:10,603
[Kim Hee Ae]
Hello.

461
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:12,772
Hello.

462
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:13,839
Over there.

463
00:21:13,839 --> 00:21:15,775
[Became Boys Again In Front Of]

464
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:17,510
- Hello.
- Hello.

465
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:19,211
[Their Childhood Star]

466
00:21:20,012 --> 00:21:21,814
I can't believe it's her.

467
00:21:24,316 --> 00:21:25,718
I'll take the towels.

468
00:21:25,718 --> 00:21:26,619
[The Barista Appears]

469
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:27,920
Thank you.

470
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,688
He's also...

471
00:21:29,688 --> 00:21:32,525
- He's also a famous guy.
- Yeah.

472
00:21:32,525 --> 00:21:35,694
What did his name tag say? Kim Seon Ho?

473
00:21:35,694 --> 00:21:36,929
Two of these.

474
00:21:36,929 --> 00:21:39,098
[Kim Seon Ho]

475
00:21:39,098 --> 00:21:40,966
What was his name?

476
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:43,269
The one wearing all black.

477
00:21:43,269 --> 00:21:44,236
- Who is it?
- Cha Seung Won.

478
00:21:44,236 --> 00:21:46,005
- Cha Seung Won.
- Right, Cha Seung Won.

479
00:21:46,005 --> 00:21:47,439
I forgot his name.

480
00:21:47,439 --> 00:21:48,941
Please wait a moment.

481
00:21:48,941 --> 00:21:50,609
[The One In Black]
[Name: Cha Seung Won]

482
00:21:50,609 --> 00:21:51,677
I'll be right there.

483
00:21:51,677 --> 00:21:53,912
[Helping The Hall Team With Orders]
Hello, please wait just a minute.

484
00:21:54,613 --> 00:21:56,916
- You're very handsome.
- Thank you.

485
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:58,250
Which dessert is good?

486
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:00,553
The dish I recommend is...

487
00:22:00,553 --> 00:22:01,887
This one is really soft.

488
00:22:01,887 --> 00:22:03,455
[Bonjour Crème Brûlée]
It's like egg custard.

489
00:22:03,455 --> 00:22:06,025
- Should we try this one?
- It's really soft.

490
00:22:06,025 --> 00:22:07,826
This one is also popular.

491
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:10,729
[Bonjour Green Barley Madeleine]
This one is new today.

492
00:22:10,729 --> 00:22:12,865
- Is it green barley?
- Yes, it's made with green barley.

493
00:22:12,865 --> 00:22:14,333
We've had too much of it.

494
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,935
You're sick of green barley?

495
00:22:15,935 --> 00:22:17,269
You should still try it.

496
00:22:17,269 --> 00:22:18,504
It's different.

497
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:19,772
- That's it for us.
- Okay.

498
00:22:19,772 --> 00:22:21,907
- We ate already.
- Got it.

499
00:22:21,907 --> 00:22:23,042
I got their order.

500
00:22:23,042 --> 00:22:24,276
Thank you!

501
00:22:24,276 --> 00:22:25,744
- I'm going back inside.
- Okay.

502
00:22:25,744 --> 00:22:28,013
- Keep up the good work.
- Great job.

503
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:29,348
- Come back later.
- Thank you.

504
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:30,516
- I will.
- Good.

505
00:22:34,854 --> 00:22:37,656
[Today's New Addition
To The Baked Goods Lineup]

506
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:39,758
[Following The Tart And Brioche]

507
00:22:39,758 --> 00:22:42,928
[The Final Dessert
In The Green Barley Series]

508
00:22:44,263 --> 00:22:47,733
[Packed With The Nutty Flavor Of Barley]

509
00:22:49,501 --> 00:22:53,438
[Bonjour Green Barley Madeleine]

510
00:22:56,942 --> 00:22:59,845
[Made With Gochang Green Barley Powder]

511
00:22:59,845 --> 00:23:02,548
[Butter And White Chocolate]

512
00:23:08,420 --> 00:23:12,157
[The Green Barley Batter
Shows A Stunning, Vibrant Green Hue]

513
00:23:16,829 --> 00:23:19,965
[Pipe 40G Of The Batter
Into Each Butter-Greased Mold]

514
00:23:19,965 --> 00:23:22,568
- How much is it?
- It's around 35 grams.

515
00:23:22,568 --> 00:23:24,470
- There we go.
- Yes.

516
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:25,938
- Hold on.
- That's exactly 40g.

517
00:23:25,938 --> 00:23:27,506
That's amazing.

518
00:23:27,506 --> 00:23:30,209
[Got The Exact Amount In One Go]

519
00:23:36,448 --> 00:23:37,583
[Exclaims]

520
00:23:38,817 --> 00:23:43,388
They're all exactly 39g or 40g.

521
00:23:47,893 --> 00:23:49,695
[Amazed]

522
00:23:50,796 --> 00:23:52,364
- All good.
- Okay.

523
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:54,266
Put that inside the freezer.

524
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,601
All right.

525
00:23:55,601 --> 00:23:57,603
- For 15 minutes?
- Yes.

526
00:23:57,603 --> 00:23:59,571
[Freeze To Rest For 15 Minutes]

527
00:23:59,571 --> 00:24:03,275
[Freezing Allows The Batter To Stabilize]

528
00:24:17,189 --> 00:24:18,590
Put them on each side.

529
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:20,426
- Okay.
- That's right.

530
00:24:20,426 --> 00:24:21,894
Just like that.

531
00:24:21,894 --> 00:24:23,462
On each side, right?

532
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:26,598
[Bars Placed Beneath The Mold]

533
00:24:26,598 --> 00:24:29,968
Do you know why we put them here?

534
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:32,905
- Do you know?
- Is it because it might droop?

535
00:24:32,905 --> 00:24:35,407
Is it because it could droop in the heat?

536
00:24:35,407 --> 00:24:37,643
[Looking At His Reaction]

537
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:39,144
[The Mold Sags In The Heat]
It becomes like this.

538
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:40,412
Then I was right.

539
00:24:40,412 --> 00:24:43,082
I said it because it might droop.

540
00:24:43,082 --> 00:24:47,052
[The Bars Prevent The Mold From Drooping]

541
00:24:47,052 --> 00:24:48,253
- Okay.
- I thought I was wrong.

542
00:24:48,253 --> 00:24:50,689
Okay, I get it.

543
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:52,358
- I said I got it.
- "I got it."

544
00:24:52,358 --> 00:24:54,927
- I thought I was wrong.
- Good for you.

545
00:24:54,927 --> 00:24:56,295
Okay.

546
00:24:58,664 --> 00:25:00,532
Put your gloves on and put it in.

547
00:25:00,532 --> 00:25:01,667
- Okay.
- All right.

548
00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:04,803
- Put it in.
- Okay.

549
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:07,139
Good.

550
00:25:13,746 --> 00:25:15,947
[The Last One Of The Madeleine Family]

551
00:25:17,383 --> 00:25:19,618
[Here Comes The Green Barley Madeleine]

552
00:25:19,618 --> 00:25:24,023
[A Good Conversation To Have
While Waiting For Dessert]

553
00:25:24,023 --> 00:25:27,493
We're from the Goryeo period, right?

554
00:25:27,493 --> 00:25:28,560
[About Their Roots]

555
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,629
My surname Ko comes from Jeju.

556
00:25:30,629 --> 00:25:32,698
They used to be royalty.

557
00:25:32,698 --> 00:25:35,934
But they lost to Goryeo.

558
00:25:35,934 --> 00:25:37,536
After the abolition of royalty,

559
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:39,304
the most capable royals

560
00:25:39,304 --> 00:25:41,507
[What Is He Saying?]
were brought back.

561
00:25:41,507 --> 00:25:43,609
As a result, top officials rise in Goryeo.

562
00:25:43,609 --> 00:25:44,777
[He's Heard It All Before Look]

563
00:25:44,777 --> 00:25:48,514
The people of Jeju never took office.

564
00:25:48,514 --> 00:25:52,084
- Others with the surname Ko...
- I don't think I can eat lunch.

565
00:25:52,084 --> 00:25:54,319
[Changing The Subject]
Did you have a big breakfast?

566
00:25:54,319 --> 00:25:56,121
You can still eat this.

567
00:25:56,121 --> 00:25:57,656
What did you have?

568
00:25:57,656 --> 00:25:59,091
I had fish stew.

569
00:25:59,091 --> 00:26:01,393
That sounds amazing.

570
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:03,028
A magnifying glass for seniors.

571
00:26:03,028 --> 00:26:06,965
You tap the surface before you eat it.

572
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:09,768
Citron and Green Barley Madeleines.

573
00:26:09,768 --> 00:26:10,836
Here are your forks.

574
00:26:10,836 --> 00:26:12,304
- You know...
- Yes?

575
00:26:12,304 --> 00:26:15,240
It's pretty cheap for all this.

576
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,375
- Right?
- Yes.

577
00:26:16,375 --> 00:26:17,676
It's cheap.

578
00:26:19,144 --> 00:26:21,980
There's a heart here,
but this one doesn't have one.

579
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:25,917
[Even 70-Year-Old Men
Care About Latte Hearts]

580
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:28,787
The coffee is good.

581
00:26:28,787 --> 00:26:31,723
[A Sip Of Sweet Vanilla Latte]

582
00:26:31,723 --> 00:26:34,593
[And A Bite Of Green Barley Madeleine]

583
00:26:37,262 --> 00:26:39,064
This is good.

584
00:26:39,064 --> 00:26:41,600
- What?
- It's delicious.

585
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,435
We like sweet stuff like this.

586
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:44,536
Yes, we do.

587
00:26:44,536 --> 00:26:46,738
[Even 70-Year-Old Men Like Sweets]

588
00:26:46,738 --> 00:26:50,308
[Scraping The Vanilla Latte Like A Hot Pot]

589
00:26:51,543 --> 00:26:53,378
And then...

590
00:26:53,378 --> 00:26:54,446
[Chugging It Down]

591
00:26:54,446 --> 00:26:56,815
Someone sent it to me.

592
00:26:56,815 --> 00:26:58,784
- You can have it.
- Let's finish it.

593
00:26:58,784 --> 00:27:00,052
[One Bite Of Madeleine Left]
Why isn't anyone having it?

594
00:27:00,052 --> 00:27:02,221
If we leave any behind,

595
00:27:02,221 --> 00:27:04,723
they'll think we didn't like it.

596
00:27:04,723 --> 00:27:06,625
Have some more.

597
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:08,861
I had fish stew, so...

598
00:27:08,861 --> 00:27:10,996
- I'm full.
- Stop bragging.

599
00:27:14,366 --> 00:27:19,738
People who are over 70 years old...

600
00:27:19,738 --> 00:27:24,877
Some still think they're in their 60s.

601
00:27:24,877 --> 00:27:25,777
Yes.

602
00:27:25,777 --> 00:27:27,679
From our point of view,

603
00:27:27,679 --> 00:27:31,049
even 63-year-olds look old on TV.

604
00:27:31,049 --> 00:27:32,818
We forget our own age.

605
00:27:32,818 --> 00:27:35,754
- You're right.
- Exactly.

606
00:27:35,754 --> 00:27:38,457
I'm shocked when I find out someone's old.

607
00:27:38,457 --> 00:27:39,858
Seriously.

608
00:27:39,858 --> 00:27:42,794
But I look old in someone else's eyes.

609
00:27:42,794 --> 00:27:45,164
It still happens even when I'm old.

610
00:27:45,164 --> 00:27:48,967
Everyone thinks they'll never get old.

611
00:27:48,967 --> 00:27:52,571
Living with that mindset isn't bad after all.

612
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:53,839
I'm going to play cards later.

613
00:27:53,839 --> 00:27:55,807
You should come visit.

614
00:27:55,807 --> 00:28:01,113
[The Gentlemen Are Heading To]

615
00:28:01,113 --> 00:28:03,081
We need spectators when playing cards.

616
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:04,616
- Exactly.
- People watching next to you.

617
00:28:04,616 --> 00:28:05,884
[The Village Hall]

618
00:28:06,718 --> 00:28:08,620
[Yesterday's Customer]

619
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:10,555
[And Today's Customer Gather Around]

620
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:13,859
[Playing Cards]

621
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:16,094
Of course.

622
00:28:16,762 --> 00:28:19,665
Of course, I'm going to win.

623
00:28:19,665 --> 00:28:22,868
These cards aren't working for me.

624
00:28:22,868 --> 00:28:24,369
It's not my day.

625
00:28:24,369 --> 00:28:26,772
- There we go.
- Darn it.

626
00:28:26,772 --> 00:28:28,774
- He's going to the bakery with the money.
- I'm going to the bakery.

627
00:28:28,774 --> 00:28:30,175
- Sorry?
- I'm going to the bakery.

628
00:28:30,175 --> 00:28:31,810
- Today?
- Yes.

629
00:28:31,810 --> 00:28:35,214
My wife is over there, so I'll bring her.

630
00:28:35,214 --> 00:28:36,949
We should visit together.

631
00:28:36,949 --> 00:28:37,883
You'd better win.

632
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:40,118
- You should head straight there.
- Why?

633
00:28:40,118 --> 00:28:41,419
<i>Now...</i>

634
00:28:45,791 --> 00:28:48,927
[Someone Visits From Next Door]

635
00:28:48,927 --> 00:28:51,263
Hello, welcome.

636
00:28:51,263 --> 00:28:53,098
How many people?

637
00:28:53,098 --> 00:28:54,666
Can I check your ID?

638
00:28:54,666 --> 00:28:56,134
You have to be over 65.

639
00:28:56,702 --> 00:28:58,370
Oh, hello!

640
00:28:58,370 --> 00:28:59,338
Oh, hello!

641
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:01,173
[Seon Ho Greets Him Enthusiastically]

642
00:29:01,173 --> 00:29:03,342
[Day 1]
Come and visit our café. We're open now.

643
00:29:03,342 --> 00:29:05,277
Are you Seon Ho?

644
00:29:05,277 --> 00:29:08,847
[He Greeted The Nervous Seon Ho
Before Opening]

645
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:11,083
[Day 2]
Let's go. Is it right next door?

646
00:29:11,083 --> 00:29:13,151
[He Ordered A Bunch Of Baked Goods To Go]

647
00:29:13,151 --> 00:29:17,756
[As Seon Ho Walked Him Outside]

648
00:29:18,724 --> 00:29:23,395
[He Brought The Baked Goods
For His Wife At The Hospital]

649
00:29:23,395 --> 00:29:24,997
Oh, hello!

650
00:29:24,997 --> 00:29:26,164
[A Visit After Being Discharged]
You're here again.

651
00:29:26,164 --> 00:29:27,699
- I'll come every day.
- Come in.

652
00:29:27,699 --> 00:29:29,534
I already checked your ID. Have a seat here.

653
00:29:29,534 --> 00:29:30,702
[No ID Check For The Regular]

654
00:29:30,702 --> 00:29:33,405
[Hyun Seon Ja, Gi Min Seon, Gi Ho Jik]

655
00:29:33,405 --> 00:29:35,340
Should we get cappuccinos?

656
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:37,175
- What?
- Cappuccinos each?

657
00:29:37,175 --> 00:29:39,811
- No.
- I don't want a cappuccino.

658
00:29:39,811 --> 00:29:42,214
- Should I get a refreshing orangeade?
- Sounds good.

659
00:29:42,214 --> 00:29:45,183
[Our Opinionated Customer's
Favorite Celeb Is...]

660
00:29:45,183 --> 00:29:46,818
One moment, please.

661
00:29:47,386 --> 00:29:50,956
I've been your fan since <i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night</i>.

662
00:29:50,956 --> 00:29:53,558
- Thank you so much.
- You're so handsome.

663
00:29:53,558 --> 00:29:54,926
What an honor.

664
00:29:56,728 --> 00:29:59,164
[How To Make Orangeade By Manager Hee Ae]

665
00:29:59,164 --> 00:30:02,501
[Pour In A Third Of A Cup Of Rich,
Fresh Orange Juice]

666
00:30:02,501 --> 00:30:04,769
[A Generous Amount Of Ice]

667
00:30:08,707 --> 00:30:13,111
[Pour The Sparkling Water
On Top To Create A Layered Look]

668
00:30:13,812 --> 00:30:16,882
[Garnish With Fresh Fruit Slices]

669
00:30:16,882 --> 00:30:20,018
[Place On Top]

670
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:26,191
[Served With The Sweet Potato Cake
They Ordered]

671
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:30,462
- Please stir with the straw.
- Okay.

672
00:30:31,296 --> 00:30:33,532
- Orangeade.
- Thank you.

673
00:30:33,532 --> 00:30:35,433
Stir it, Dad.

674
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:38,670
It sinks to the bottom.

675
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:40,138
This is good.

676
00:30:42,107 --> 00:30:44,476
[A Big Scoop Of Sweet Potato Cake]

677
00:30:49,214 --> 00:30:50,682
[Glances Over]

678
00:30:51,583 --> 00:30:53,785
How is it? Do you like it?

679
00:30:53,785 --> 00:30:55,654
How is it? Do you like it?

680
00:30:55,654 --> 00:30:56,955
Really?

681
00:30:59,024 --> 00:31:00,859
After we eat this,

682
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:04,796
we should get some more to take home
so we can get the bag.

683
00:31:04,796 --> 00:31:08,066
[The Baked Goods Lineup Changes Every Day]

684
00:31:08,767 --> 00:31:11,970
[They're Great For Sharing With Loved Ones]

685
00:31:12,838 --> 00:31:16,675
[And If You Order It To Go,
We Put It In A Cute Canvas Bag]

686
00:31:16,675 --> 00:31:18,810
[Bonjour Bakery]

687
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:21,346
- Would you like one of each?
- Yes.

688
00:31:21,346 --> 00:31:23,148
Please wait a moment.

689
00:31:23,148 --> 00:31:24,282
[With To-Go Orders Pouring In]

690
00:31:24,282 --> 00:31:27,452
[It's Time To Make More Financiers]

691
00:31:27,452 --> 00:31:29,654
[Pre-Heating The Oven]

692
00:31:29,654 --> 00:31:31,356
The baked goods are flying off the shelves.

693
00:31:31,356 --> 00:31:32,858
We keep running out of them.

694
00:31:32,858 --> 00:31:35,460
I keep refilling them,
but they're gone in no time.

695
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:37,162
They're a big hit.

696
00:31:37,162 --> 00:31:40,365
Three minutes in the oven.

697
00:31:40,365 --> 00:31:41,266
That's hot.

698
00:31:41,266 --> 00:31:43,168
[Two Pans Of Financiers Go In]

699
00:31:43,168 --> 00:31:46,471
[First Bake For 3 Minutes]

700
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:48,840
They're a hit.

701
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:51,042
We run out every time I refill them.

702
00:31:51,042 --> 00:31:53,545
[Spreading Words About Baked Goods]
I feel so proud.

703
00:31:53,545 --> 00:31:54,980
[Goes Out Once Again]

704
00:31:54,980 --> 00:31:56,281
Excuse me.

705
00:31:59,117 --> 00:32:01,153
[They're Empty Again]

706
00:32:01,153 --> 00:32:03,021
We need more citron.

707
00:32:03,021 --> 00:32:04,356
Bokbunja and citron.

708
00:32:04,356 --> 00:32:05,424
[Mumbling To Himself]

709
00:32:05,424 --> 00:32:07,592
[It's Been 3 Minutes!]

710
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:13,364
[Flip The Pans So They Cook Evenly]

711
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:19,437
Between the oven and everything else,
there's a lot going on.

712
00:32:21,039 --> 00:32:23,942
But it's so much fun.

713
00:32:25,210 --> 00:32:27,979
[Learning The Joy Of Filling It Up]

714
00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:29,414
[Did You Know?]

715
00:32:29,414 --> 00:32:32,383
[Financier Means Gold Bar]

716
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:39,457
[Ki Taek's Pan Of Happiness
Is Baked To A Golden Color]

717
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:43,228
[Cooling Them On A Wire Rack
Allows The Surface To Evaporate]

718
00:32:43,228 --> 00:32:46,631
[Making The Outside Crisp
And The Inside Chewy]

719
00:32:50,368 --> 00:32:53,038
[Customers Waiting For The Baked Goods]

720
00:32:53,038 --> 00:32:56,508
[Gong Jeong Im, Yeom Sun Hee]

721
00:32:58,109 --> 00:33:01,079
[Keep Glancing Around]

722
00:33:01,079 --> 00:33:04,950
[As If This Place Is Unfamiliar To Them]

723
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:07,285
They'll come take our order.

724
00:33:07,285 --> 00:33:10,522
- What?
- They'll come take our order.

725
00:33:10,522 --> 00:33:13,492
I was just looking around.

726
00:33:13,492 --> 00:33:16,495
She's a famous actress.

727
00:33:16,495 --> 00:33:17,863
[Calmly Explaining Everything]

728
00:33:17,863 --> 00:33:19,931
She'll come over

729
00:33:19,931 --> 00:33:22,100
and ask us what we want.

730
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:23,101
[Someone Accompanying Her]

731
00:33:23,101 --> 00:33:25,504
- Hello.
- Hello.

732
00:33:25,504 --> 00:33:27,472
- Hello, ma'am.
- Hello.

733
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:29,808
It's cold, isn't it? This is for your hands.

734
00:33:29,808 --> 00:33:32,110
Please take your time with the menu.

735
00:33:33,612 --> 00:33:35,079
Go ahead.

736
00:33:36,047 --> 00:33:37,882
[Wipe]

737
00:33:40,352 --> 00:33:41,920
Look at the flowers.

738
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,989
Daffodils.

739
00:33:43,989 --> 00:33:46,691
They did a good job decorating this place.

740
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:51,696
[Takes The Used Towel]

741
00:33:52,664 --> 00:33:54,866
[Folds It Neatly]

742
00:33:54,866 --> 00:33:56,034
You must be hungry.

743
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:58,470
I know you don't like to wait.

744
00:33:58,470 --> 00:34:00,438
I'm not hungry.

745
00:34:00,438 --> 00:34:03,308
But I'm glad we came here.

746
00:34:03,308 --> 00:34:04,609
The weather's beautiful today.

747
00:34:04,609 --> 00:34:07,245
- Yes, it's warm.
- Yes.

748
00:34:07,245 --> 00:34:08,847
When will I visit a place like this again?

749
00:34:08,847 --> 00:34:11,749
I'm here thanks to you.

750
00:34:13,251 --> 00:34:15,153
[You Should Enjoy The View]

751
00:34:16,488 --> 00:34:19,657
[With A Sweet Dessert]

752
00:34:20,225 --> 00:34:22,327
[When Serving A Full Tray]

753
00:34:22,327 --> 00:34:25,597
[He Goes Across The Counter]

754
00:34:26,264 --> 00:34:27,299
[To Deliver It Safely]

755
00:34:27,299 --> 00:34:29,100
Here you are.

756
00:34:29,834 --> 00:34:31,870
I'll leave the forks here.

757
00:34:32,571 --> 00:34:36,041
[Chamomile]
This tea helps you sleep at night.

758
00:34:36,041 --> 00:34:39,411
That's why I ordered it.

759
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:42,313
It will help you sleep soundly.

760
00:34:46,251 --> 00:34:48,586
[Cuts Them Into Bite-Size Pieces]

761
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:51,756
Here, try this.

762
00:34:51,756 --> 00:34:53,124
Stab it.

763
00:34:54,059 --> 00:34:56,027
It looks hard, but it's soft.

764
00:35:10,275 --> 00:35:12,844
[Try Some Madeleines As Well]

765
00:35:14,713 --> 00:35:16,514
I'll end up eating it all.

766
00:35:16,514 --> 00:35:19,317
I cut them for you.

767
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:20,819
I love the coffee.

768
00:35:20,819 --> 00:35:21,720
- You do?
- Yes.

769
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:23,388
- I made it.
- Thank you.

770
00:35:23,388 --> 00:35:25,123
I'm in charge of the coffee.

771
00:35:25,123 --> 00:35:26,257
It's great.

772
00:35:27,359 --> 00:35:29,194
She's very old.

773
00:35:29,194 --> 00:35:30,929
- She's over 90 years old.
- What?

774
00:35:31,930 --> 00:35:33,498
You look young for your age.

775
00:35:33,498 --> 00:35:34,833
- Me?
- Yes.

776
00:35:34,833 --> 00:35:36,635
- Your hair--
- I've had back and knee surgeries.

777
00:35:36,635 --> 00:35:38,536
- And I can't hear well.
- I see.

778
00:35:38,536 --> 00:35:40,038
I'm very old.

779
00:35:40,038 --> 00:35:41,840
Do you have an appetite?

780
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,441
Are you eating well?

781
00:35:43,441 --> 00:35:45,443
I eat every meal.

782
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:48,480
My mother has no appetite.

783
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:50,482
She can't enjoy food.

784
00:35:50,482 --> 00:35:51,716
How old is she?

785
00:35:51,716 --> 00:35:54,252
She's 86 years old.

786
00:35:54,252 --> 00:35:55,587
What?

787
00:35:55,587 --> 00:35:56,655
- She's 86...
- She can't hear very well.

788
00:35:56,655 --> 00:35:59,457
She's 86 years old.

789
00:36:00,458 --> 00:36:04,596
It was nice to come here, right?

790
00:36:04,596 --> 00:36:06,831
She's my caretaker.

791
00:36:06,831 --> 00:36:08,633
I see.

792
00:36:08,633 --> 00:36:11,169
She said we should come here,

793
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:12,704
so I got ready right away.

794
00:36:12,704 --> 00:36:14,673
- I'm glad you came.
- I needed some air.

795
00:36:14,673 --> 00:36:16,875
Yes, I'm so glad.

796
00:36:16,875 --> 00:36:18,610
[The Two Of Them Would]

797
00:36:18,610 --> 00:36:21,446
[Go On A Stroll Every Time Spring Came]

798
00:36:21,446 --> 00:36:23,248
- Thank you. Take care.
- Two <i>Bokbunja</i>.

799
00:36:23,248 --> 00:36:25,884
- Take care. Thank you.
- Thank you.

800
00:36:25,884 --> 00:36:29,854
[When They Look Back On This Spring]

801
00:36:31,956 --> 00:36:36,694
[How Will They Remember The Bakery?]
One, two, three.

802
00:36:37,929 --> 00:36:41,900
[Bonjour Bakery]

803
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:44,736
[1:00 P.M.]

804
00:36:44,736 --> 00:36:45,870
[People Are Waiting To Get In]

805
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:47,605
Can you take a photo with my camera?

806
00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:49,174
- I'll take it with mine.
- Okay.

807
00:36:49,174 --> 00:36:51,509
Look over there, Grandma.

808
00:36:51,509 --> 00:36:52,410
[Go Over There?]

809
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,511
Come here.

810
00:36:53,511 --> 00:36:55,046
[No, Look Over There]

811
00:36:55,046 --> 00:36:57,415
- Stand here?
- Make a peace sign.

812
00:36:57,415 --> 00:37:02,020
[A Mirror Selfie With The Granddaughter]

813
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:05,390
[While The Customers Take Photos]

814
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:08,493
[Seon Ho Quickly Cleans The Tables]

815
00:37:08,493 --> 00:37:12,964
[Never Forgets To Disinfect]

816
00:37:13,832 --> 00:37:15,700
[Clean]

817
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:18,570
[Okay, We're Ready]

818
00:37:18,570 --> 00:37:20,505
Is there a Kim Sun Bok?

819
00:37:20,505 --> 00:37:21,873
Kim Ae Su?

820
00:37:22,474 --> 00:37:23,508
Yes.

821
00:37:23,508 --> 00:37:24,509
[Customers Go In]

822
00:37:24,509 --> 00:37:26,211
Please take a seat there.

823
00:37:26,211 --> 00:37:29,114
- We'll have one hot Americano.
- Okay.

824
00:37:29,114 --> 00:37:31,116
- One vanilla latte.
- Okay.

825
00:37:31,116 --> 00:37:34,219
Green Barley Field Tart and Camellia Tart.

826
00:37:34,219 --> 00:37:35,820
- It's so nice.
- It is.

827
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:38,223
They made the place look so cute inside.

828
00:37:38,223 --> 00:37:40,058
You're right.

829
00:37:40,058 --> 00:37:42,761
I get to come here thanks to you.

830
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:45,096
- No, I'm here thanks to you.
- It's so nice.

831
00:37:45,096 --> 00:37:47,832
Otherwise, I couldn't even come inside.

832
00:37:47,832 --> 00:37:48,867
We came together.

833
00:37:48,867 --> 00:37:50,602
[Spending Time With The Granddaughter]

834
00:37:50,602 --> 00:37:54,172
[Hee Ae Gets Ready To Take Orders]

835
00:37:54,172 --> 00:37:57,275
[She Takes The Order Sheet]

836
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:59,677
- Hello.
- Hello.

837
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:00,745
[And Heads To Table 2?]

838
00:38:00,745 --> 00:38:02,213
They already ordered.

839
00:38:02,213 --> 00:38:03,448
It's that table there, Hee Ae.

840
00:38:03,448 --> 00:38:04,916
- We already ordered.
- We already ordered.

841
00:38:04,916 --> 00:38:07,085
Sorry about that.

842
00:38:07,085 --> 00:38:08,519
[Hurries Over]

843
00:38:10,054 --> 00:38:12,490
- Hello.
- Hello.

844
00:38:12,490 --> 00:38:16,861
We'll have one iced vanilla latte.

845
00:38:16,861 --> 00:38:18,329
A hot cappuccino.

846
00:38:18,329 --> 00:38:21,499
One Green Barley Field Tart.

847
00:38:21,499 --> 00:38:25,002
[Prepares The Desserts Right Away]

848
00:38:28,072 --> 00:38:30,475
Do you need the Sweet Potato Cake now?

849
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:32,210
- Do you need it right now?
- Yes.

850
00:38:32,210 --> 00:38:33,211
We need to cut it.

851
00:38:33,211 --> 00:38:34,379
Ask them to wait a little.

852
00:38:34,379 --> 00:38:35,780
Which table? I'll bring it.

853
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:36,915
That one.

854
00:38:36,915 --> 00:38:39,651
- The one at the end.
- Over there?

855
00:38:39,651 --> 00:38:42,720
[Seung Won Goes To Serve The Big Table]

856
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,189
No, not over there.

857
00:38:44,189 --> 00:38:45,089
It's here.

858
00:38:45,089 --> 00:38:47,225
What? I sent him there.

859
00:38:47,225 --> 00:38:49,093
- It's over here.
- The three desserts?

860
00:38:49,093 --> 00:38:50,094
- Are these for you?
- I'm sorry.

861
00:38:50,094 --> 00:38:51,362
The crème brûlée and...

862
00:38:51,362 --> 00:38:52,764
I mixed them up.

863
00:38:52,764 --> 00:38:54,032
Just one moment, please.

864
00:38:54,032 --> 00:38:55,600
It got them confused.

865
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:56,834
[It's Okay]

866
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:02,173
Green Barley Tart.

867
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:03,575
This one's ready.

868
00:39:03,575 --> 00:39:04,576
[Seung Won Hurries To Help Hee Ae]

869
00:39:04,576 --> 00:39:06,211
Here you are. Sorry about that.

870
00:39:06,211 --> 00:39:07,111
- It's fine.
- It's okay.

871
00:39:07,111 --> 00:39:09,614
This one is really popular.

872
00:39:09,614 --> 00:39:11,683
- These two are our signature desserts.
- Exactly.

873
00:39:11,683 --> 00:39:14,185
It's also the hardest to make.

874
00:39:14,185 --> 00:39:15,954
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

875
00:39:15,954 --> 00:39:19,090
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

876
00:39:21,693 --> 00:39:23,895
[Sighs]

877
00:39:27,265 --> 00:39:28,933
Is everything okay?

878
00:39:28,933 --> 00:39:30,535
I'm fine.

879
00:39:30,535 --> 00:39:34,405
[Hee Ae Is Bothered By Her Mistakes]

880
00:39:34,405 --> 00:39:36,941
Don't worry about it.

881
00:39:43,548 --> 00:39:47,151
[What Does Chef Cha Have To Do Right Now?]

882
00:39:47,151 --> 00:39:52,056
[Make Something To Cheer Hee Ae Up]

883
00:39:52,056 --> 00:39:55,293
[It Needs To Be Exceptionally Good Today]

884
00:39:55,293 --> 00:39:58,830
[It's Time To Make The Legendary Curry]

885
00:39:58,830 --> 00:40:00,164
[1 Pack Of Spicy Curry]

886
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:02,367
[2 Packs Of Spicy Curry]

887
00:40:02,367 --> 00:40:04,168
[1 Pack Of Mild Curry]

888
00:40:04,168 --> 00:40:06,604
[1 Pack Of Medium Spicy Curry]

889
00:40:06,604 --> 00:40:09,107
[2 Packs Of Medium Spicy Curry]

890
00:40:09,107 --> 00:40:10,508
[Chef Cha's Curry Tip]

891
00:40:10,508 --> 00:40:13,778
[Create A Rich Flavor
By Mixing Three Curries]

892
00:40:17,215 --> 00:40:20,017
[Preparing Ingredients For The Curry]

893
00:40:20,852 --> 00:40:25,089
[Ki Taek Watches Silently]

894
00:40:26,057 --> 00:40:28,092
[He Takes Out A Large Plate]

895
00:40:31,729 --> 00:40:34,232
[And Gets It Ready For The Onions]

896
00:40:35,633 --> 00:40:39,137
[But They Go Straight Into The Pot]

897
00:40:39,137 --> 00:40:41,806
[What?]

898
00:40:41,806 --> 00:40:45,409
[Returns The Plate]

899
00:40:46,477 --> 00:40:50,681
[Cut Each Ingredient To The Same Size]

900
00:40:54,886 --> 00:40:58,289
[And Add A Yellow Blob?]

901
00:40:58,289 --> 00:41:01,225
[It's Butter!]

902
00:41:01,225 --> 00:41:06,331
[Chef Cha's Curry Tip]
[Add Butter To Increase The Flavor]

903
00:41:06,331 --> 00:41:08,599
[Adds A Ton Of Sirloin]

904
00:41:10,234 --> 00:41:13,304
[Lots Of Protein For The Manager]

905
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:20,311
[Cook The Ingredients]

906
00:41:24,115 --> 00:41:28,519
[The Curry Powder He Mixed Earlier]

907
00:41:28,519 --> 00:41:34,158
[Stir To Prevent It From Sticking To The Pot]

908
00:41:39,630 --> 00:41:40,932
- Ki Taek.
- Yes?

909
00:41:40,932 --> 00:41:43,134
- Come here.
- Okay.

910
00:41:43,134 --> 00:41:45,470
- Let me know if it's too salty.
- All right.

911
00:41:45,470 --> 00:41:47,605
It's hot, so be careful.

912
00:41:55,446 --> 00:41:56,414
- It's perfect.
- Is it?

913
00:41:56,414 --> 00:41:58,182
- Yes.
- Okay, got it.

914
00:41:58,182 --> 00:42:00,184
- Right? That's done.
- Yes.

915
00:42:00,184 --> 00:42:05,189
[While They Make The Curry
To Cheer Up The Manager]

916
00:42:05,189 --> 00:42:07,592
[The Grandma And Granddaughter
Enjoy Their Dessert]

917
00:42:07,592 --> 00:42:09,093
I'm so happy, Grandma.

918
00:42:09,093 --> 00:42:11,029
Take a photo.

919
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:14,098
[Click]

920
00:42:14,098 --> 00:42:15,867
Can you pose for me?

921
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:17,135
Right now?

922
00:42:17,135 --> 00:42:18,369
- That's enough.
- It'll show up.

923
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:20,338
- That's enough.
- Come on.

924
00:42:20,338 --> 00:42:23,508
[Tells Her To Stop But Poses For Her]

925
00:42:23,508 --> 00:42:26,010
[Gen Z Shot With The Granddaughter]

926
00:42:26,010 --> 00:42:27,378
It's a shame to eat it.

927
00:42:29,714 --> 00:42:31,182
- Want to make a toast?
- Let's cheers.

928
00:42:31,182 --> 00:42:32,350
Cheers!

929
00:42:32,350 --> 00:42:34,485
[Cheers With Coffee]

930
00:42:34,485 --> 00:42:36,320
Is there anywhere you want to go?

931
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:37,455
Why do you ask?

932
00:42:37,455 --> 00:42:39,757
Since the weather's so nice.

933
00:42:39,757 --> 00:42:42,293
I'll be gone for a while after next week.

934
00:42:42,293 --> 00:42:43,728
You're going back next week?

935
00:42:43,728 --> 00:42:46,831
I think so.

936
00:42:46,831 --> 00:42:49,133
Do you want me to stay here forever?

937
00:42:49,734 --> 00:42:53,938
[Grandma Is Sad To See Her Leave For Work]

938
00:42:53,938 --> 00:42:56,240
- It's just...
- I'll come back in two years.

939
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:58,709
I'll work hard for two years.

940
00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:01,012
Do your best.

941
00:43:01,012 --> 00:43:02,346
Work hard.

942
00:43:02,346 --> 00:43:06,317
[Roots For Her Granddaughter's Future
Despite The Sadness]

943
00:43:07,018 --> 00:43:08,820
[The Two Make Some Precious Memories]

944
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:11,522
- I did it.
- Good job.

945
00:43:11,522 --> 00:43:14,892
[Just Then, Someone Enters The Bakery]

946
00:43:16,227 --> 00:43:17,795
Did you leave something behind?

947
00:43:17,795 --> 00:43:19,897
- No, I need to pay.
- You didn't pay?

948
00:43:19,897 --> 00:43:21,732
[The Customer From Earlier]
The madeleine from earlier.

949
00:43:21,732 --> 00:43:24,702
[The Madeleine?]

950
00:43:24,702 --> 00:43:28,806
- I came with my mother earlier.
- Yes.

951
00:43:28,806 --> 00:43:32,076
I bought 8, but we received 16.

952
00:43:32,076 --> 00:43:34,879
You ordered 8, but we gave you 16.

953
00:43:34,879 --> 00:43:37,014
- Yes.
- I did that?

954
00:43:37,014 --> 00:43:41,486
Green barley, <i>bokbunja</i>, citron, and bonjour.

955
00:43:41,486 --> 00:43:42,620
[Ordered 2 Of Each Item]
Two of each.

956
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:43,855
[8 In Total]
Is that eight?

957
00:43:43,855 --> 00:43:45,823
- Yes.
- Okay.

958
00:43:45,823 --> 00:43:48,292
[Hee Ae Packed Them One By One]

959
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:50,161
[2 Financiers]

960
00:43:50,161 --> 00:43:54,232
[But She Grabs More?]

961
00:43:54,232 --> 00:43:56,600
[And Then Another One?]

962
00:43:58,069 --> 00:44:02,006
[She Put 8 In Each Box]

963
00:44:03,841 --> 00:44:04,742
[Packed Two Times The Amount]

964
00:44:04,742 --> 00:44:07,712
- Stay healthy, ma'am.
- Thank you.

965
00:44:07,712 --> 00:44:10,681
[Speechless At Her Mistake]

966
00:44:10,681 --> 00:44:13,317
- So I came back to pay.
- Wait.

967
00:44:14,418 --> 00:44:16,354
Don't worry. It's on us.

968
00:44:16,354 --> 00:44:17,922
Don't worry. It's on us.

969
00:44:17,922 --> 00:44:19,557
[Seon Ho Covers For Hee Ae's Mistake]

970
00:44:19,557 --> 00:44:20,992
To celebrate your mother's recovery.

971
00:44:20,992 --> 00:44:22,627
- Her recovery?
- Yes.

972
00:44:22,627 --> 00:44:23,961
Come again next week.

973
00:44:23,961 --> 00:44:26,831
I opened the box,
and there was more than I expected.

974
00:44:26,831 --> 00:44:28,432
- So I came to pay.
- It's fine.

975
00:44:28,432 --> 00:44:29,600
Don't worry.

976
00:44:29,600 --> 00:44:31,936
Please come again next week.

977
00:44:31,936 --> 00:44:34,639
I'm very clumsy.

978
00:44:34,639 --> 00:44:37,408
- But it worked out for the best.
- I guess.

979
00:44:37,408 --> 00:44:39,977
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

980
00:44:39,977 --> 00:44:41,579
[Walk Ho Jik's Daughter Out]
Thank you.

981
00:44:41,579 --> 00:44:44,015
- I made you come all this way.
- It's right next door.

982
00:44:44,015 --> 00:44:45,816
- It's okay.
- Take care.

983
00:44:50,955 --> 00:44:52,690
- Hee Ae.
- Yes?

984
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:54,025
Good job.

985
00:44:54,025 --> 00:44:56,527
Now that's good service.

986
00:44:56,527 --> 00:44:58,262
I want to cry.

987
00:44:58,262 --> 00:45:00,665
I hate myself.

988
00:45:00,665 --> 00:45:05,503
In a cramped space like this,
things can get chaotic.

989
00:45:05,503 --> 00:45:07,338
That's what happened.

990
00:45:07,338 --> 00:45:11,242
It was actually great today, Hee Ae.

991
00:45:11,242 --> 00:45:14,845
The orangeades turned out perfectly.

992
00:45:14,845 --> 00:45:17,481
[Seon Ho Comforts Her Sincerely]
No matter what you say...

993
00:45:17,481 --> 00:45:20,050
- Come on, Hee Ae.
- I want to cry.

994
00:45:22,486 --> 00:45:23,621
You got this!

995
00:45:24,789 --> 00:45:26,590
- Hee Ae.
- Yes?

996
00:45:29,126 --> 00:45:32,263
It's not just 1 or 2.
How could I mistake 8 for 16?

997
00:45:32,263 --> 00:45:34,332
I can't even do simple math anymore.

998
00:45:34,332 --> 00:45:35,666
- I can't believe this.
- It's okay.

999
00:45:35,666 --> 00:45:38,436
It happens when things get hectic.

1000
00:45:38,436 --> 00:45:42,807
[She Keeps Making Mistakes Today]

1001
00:45:42,807 --> 00:45:44,275
- We already ordered.
- We already ordered.

1002
00:45:44,275 --> 00:45:45,676
Sorry about that.

1003
00:45:45,676 --> 00:45:48,613
[These Small, Silly Mistakes]

1004
00:45:48,613 --> 00:45:51,015
No, not over there. It's here.

1005
00:45:51,015 --> 00:45:53,851
What? I sent him there.

1006
00:45:53,851 --> 00:45:56,387
- I'm sorry.
- The crème brûlée and...

1007
00:45:56,387 --> 00:45:58,556
You seem really busy.

1008
00:45:58,556 --> 00:45:59,957
I'm losing my mind.

1009
00:45:59,957 --> 00:46:02,193
It must be really hectic.

1010
00:46:02,193 --> 00:46:04,828
[Things Keep Adding Up Today]

1011
00:46:11,502 --> 00:46:13,638
- At least she enjoyed it.
- Yeah.

1012
00:46:13,638 --> 00:46:14,772
Happy ending.

1013
00:46:14,772 --> 00:46:15,773
Okay!

1014
00:46:15,773 --> 00:46:17,275
Okay!

1015
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:19,110
- You'll feel better once we eat.
- Yes.

1016
00:46:19,110 --> 00:46:22,246
- We have the salted oysters.
- You're right.

1017
00:46:22,246 --> 00:46:23,914
[Break Time]

1018
00:46:23,914 --> 00:46:25,416
- Should we eat?
- Yes.

1019
00:46:25,416 --> 00:46:26,317
Let's eat.

1020
00:46:26,317 --> 00:46:29,820
Come on, let's eat.

1021
00:46:29,820 --> 00:46:31,622
[On Break]

1022
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:32,623
It's actually...

1023
00:46:32,623 --> 00:46:33,991
This is for Hee Ae.

1024
00:46:33,991 --> 00:46:36,193
- It takes a lot of work.
- Thank you.

1025
00:46:36,193 --> 00:46:37,528
[An Extra Pretty Plate For Hee Ae]

1026
00:46:37,528 --> 00:46:39,663
Are we at a restaurant in Japan?

1027
00:46:40,698 --> 00:46:42,933
Do you want white rice or brown rice?

1028
00:46:42,933 --> 00:46:44,368
- Either one is fine.
- Really?

1029
00:46:44,368 --> 00:46:45,936
- I'll have white rice today.
- Eat white rice today.

1030
00:46:45,936 --> 00:46:47,338
- White rice is good.
- White rice.

1031
00:46:47,338 --> 00:46:48,472
White rice.

1032
00:46:48,472 --> 00:46:50,274
[Seon Ho Chooses White Rice]

1033
00:46:50,274 --> 00:46:52,209
Eat some white rice.

1034
00:46:52,943 --> 00:46:55,012
[Bursts Out Laughing]

1035
00:46:55,012 --> 00:46:57,515
- What?
- You make me...

1036
00:46:57,515 --> 00:47:00,985
- What?
- You make me laugh, Chef Cha.

1037
00:47:00,985 --> 00:47:02,853
[Chef Cha Lightens Things Up With A Joke]
Have some white rice, please.

1038
00:47:02,853 --> 00:47:04,255
I like white rice.

1039
00:47:04,255 --> 00:47:07,224
- Yes, you have to eat white rice.
- I agree.

1040
00:47:08,592 --> 00:47:12,529
[The Kitchen Team Plates The Food In Bowls]

1041
00:47:15,099 --> 00:47:17,001
Let me try just the curry.

1042
00:47:17,001 --> 00:47:18,636
I tried it earlier, and it's amazing.

1043
00:47:23,174 --> 00:47:28,812
[Soothing The Tired Mind With Delicious Food]

1044
00:47:34,218 --> 00:47:35,853
What is this radish kimchi?

1045
00:47:35,853 --> 00:47:37,421
- This one?
- Where did you get it?

1046
00:47:37,421 --> 00:47:39,723
- At the traditional market.
- Yeah.

1047
00:47:48,232 --> 00:47:51,602
- Did you combine three curries?
- Yes.

1048
00:47:51,602 --> 00:47:53,604
- Mild, regular, and spicy?
- Yes.

1049
00:47:53,604 --> 00:47:56,140
And Vermont Curry, if possible.

1050
00:47:57,274 --> 00:47:59,343
- You like fried anchovies, don't you?
- Yes.

1051
00:47:59,343 --> 00:48:00,311
They're so good.

1052
00:48:00,311 --> 00:48:01,879
They're good.

1053
00:48:01,879 --> 00:48:03,280
Thank you.

1054
00:48:03,280 --> 00:48:07,852
Your mother is a great cook.

1055
00:48:07,852 --> 00:48:09,086
There's more, Seon Ho.

1056
00:48:09,086 --> 00:48:10,755
[Have Some More]

1057
00:48:10,755 --> 00:48:12,723
Me too.

1058
00:48:19,563 --> 00:48:21,031
I had no idea.

1059
00:48:21,031 --> 00:48:24,568
I hoped for it,

1060
00:48:24,568 --> 00:48:26,937
but didn't expect your cooking every day.

1061
00:48:26,937 --> 00:48:28,406
Really.

1062
00:48:28,406 --> 00:48:31,142
- I have to eat, too.
- You must be tired.

1063
00:48:31,142 --> 00:48:33,344
- I have to eat.
- I didn't expect it.

1064
00:48:33,344 --> 00:48:35,212
- It's nice to eat together.
- Thank you.

1065
00:48:35,212 --> 00:48:37,415
People who cook are very selfless.

1066
00:48:37,415 --> 00:48:40,651
Preparing a meal gets harder and harder.

1067
00:48:40,651 --> 00:48:42,820
It takes more work than eating alone.

1068
00:48:50,561 --> 00:48:51,962
Goodness.

1069
00:48:56,801 --> 00:48:58,502
That was a great meal.

1070
00:48:59,537 --> 00:49:02,039
- Thanks for the meal.
- Thank you.

1071
00:49:16,921 --> 00:49:21,291
[Seon Ho Adds Items
To The Afternoon Signature Menu]

1072
00:49:29,867 --> 00:49:31,235
Hello.

1073
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:33,971
Hello.

1074
00:49:33,971 --> 00:49:35,639
[Ran Into Mr. Gi Ho Jik Again]
Did you enjoy the dessert earlier?

1075
00:49:35,639 --> 00:49:38,209
We were so busy, I didn't get to talk to you.

1076
00:49:38,209 --> 00:49:39,977
She went to pay for the madeleines.

1077
00:49:39,977 --> 00:49:41,912
There was no need.

1078
00:49:41,912 --> 00:49:43,481
- You'll come again, right?
- What?

1079
00:49:43,481 --> 00:49:46,283
- You'll come again, right?
- Of course.

1080
00:49:46,283 --> 00:49:47,852
What's planned for tomorrow?

1081
00:49:47,852 --> 00:49:49,153
- What?
- Are you closed tomorrow?

1082
00:49:49,153 --> 00:49:51,655
Yes, we're closed. We'll be back next week.

1083
00:49:51,655 --> 00:49:53,724
- Next week?
- Yes, please come then.

1084
00:49:53,724 --> 00:49:58,028
Okay, I'll come visit all the time.

1085
00:49:58,028 --> 00:49:59,730
Okay, take care.

1086
00:50:03,133 --> 00:50:06,337
[From The Take-Out Frenzy In The Morning]

1087
00:50:06,337 --> 00:50:08,472
[Bonjour Pecan Paris-Brest]

1088
00:50:08,472 --> 00:50:13,677
[Another Dessert Is Added
To The Afternoon Menu]

1089
00:50:17,414 --> 00:50:19,617
[We Are Open]

1090
00:50:19,617 --> 00:50:25,255
[Who Will Visit In The Afternoon?]

1091
00:50:28,058 --> 00:50:32,196
[Preparing The Additional Menu]

1092
00:50:32,997 --> 00:50:36,967
[This Pastry Looks Like A Butter Cookie]

1093
00:50:36,967 --> 00:50:40,270
[One Of France's Most Iconic Desserts]
[The Pecan Paris-Brest]

1094
00:50:41,005 --> 00:50:47,144
[Originally Created To Commemorate
A Bicycle Race Between Paris And Brest]

1095
00:50:47,144 --> 00:50:50,380
[A Round, Ring-Like Shape
That Looks Like A Bicycle Wheel]

1096
00:50:50,948 --> 00:50:55,385
[Sweet Cream Piled High
Over A Crisp Choux Pastry]

1097
00:50:55,986 --> 00:50:57,955
[The Special Kick
In Bonjour Bakery's Version]

1098
00:50:57,955 --> 00:50:59,323
[Gochang Pecans]

1099
00:50:59,323 --> 00:51:04,795
[And Syrup Made From Pecans]

1100
00:51:06,664 --> 00:51:09,399
[Pipe The Dough Into A Ring]

1101
00:51:11,468 --> 00:51:16,039
[Follow The Guidelines To Pipe It Evenly]

1102
00:51:18,342 --> 00:51:21,412
[Hunched Over]

1103
00:51:21,412 --> 00:51:24,281
[The Perfection Of The Ring Might Be]

1104
00:51:24,281 --> 00:51:28,452
[Directly Proportional
To How Much You Bend Your Waist]

1105
00:51:30,287 --> 00:51:33,090
[Bending Down Like A Ripe Stalk Of Rice]

1106
00:51:33,090 --> 00:51:35,225
[Grunts]

1107
00:51:42,166 --> 00:51:43,934
[A Total Of 35 Piping Per Pan]

1108
00:51:43,934 --> 00:51:45,569
- Okay.
- Yes.

1109
00:51:46,403 --> 00:51:48,105
Okay.

1110
00:51:48,105 --> 00:51:50,774
[Freeze For 15 Minutes]

1111
00:51:51,375 --> 00:51:53,844
- Those rings are harder than they look.
- You're right.

1112
00:51:53,844 --> 00:51:54,912
My back hurts so much.

1113
00:51:54,912 --> 00:51:57,281
Yes, it hurts your back.

1114
00:51:57,281 --> 00:52:01,485
[Freeze The Dough For 15 Minutes,
Then Bake At 170 Degrees For 40 Minutes]

1115
00:52:01,485 --> 00:52:04,254
[The Craquelin Melts,
Covering The Choux Dough]

1116
00:52:13,497 --> 00:52:16,667
[Baked To A Gorgeous, Golden-Brown]

1117
00:52:16,667 --> 00:52:17,568
[Pipe The Cream Fillings]

1118
00:52:17,568 --> 00:52:19,970
[Pipe The Cream Fillings Inside The Choux]

1119
00:52:20,871 --> 00:52:24,574
[Filling 1]
[Vanilla Cream]

1120
00:52:28,245 --> 00:52:29,947
[Filling 2]

1121
00:52:29,947 --> 00:52:32,449
[Sweet Pecan Syrup
On Top Of The Vanilla Cream]

1122
00:52:36,153 --> 00:52:40,257
[An Ingredient Made
By Caramelizing Pecans And Sugar]

1123
00:52:40,257 --> 00:52:44,194
[Filling 3]
[Fill To The Top With Vanilla Cream]

1124
00:52:49,967 --> 00:52:53,837
[Once 3-Step Filling Process Is Complete]

1125
00:52:55,239 --> 00:52:58,342
[Another Cream Appears]

1126
00:53:02,546 --> 00:53:05,282
This doesn't look good.

1127
00:53:07,184 --> 00:53:08,619
[Slippery]

1128
00:53:08,619 --> 00:53:09,753
[Flustered]

1129
00:53:11,121 --> 00:53:13,090
[Deals With It As If It's Nothing New]

1130
00:53:13,090 --> 00:53:15,426
- Give it to me.
- Okay.

1131
00:53:15,426 --> 00:53:17,461
- Darn it.
- I know, right?

1132
00:53:17,461 --> 00:53:19,930
It wasn't done properly.

1133
00:53:22,166 --> 00:53:24,167
Do it over.

1134
00:53:24,802 --> 00:53:26,136
Should I start over?

1135
00:53:26,136 --> 00:53:27,171
It's fine.

1136
00:53:27,171 --> 00:53:28,839
[Worried]

1137
00:53:28,839 --> 00:53:30,340
[Blinking]
Come on.

1138
00:53:30,340 --> 00:53:32,576
I can't even tie this.

1139
00:53:35,012 --> 00:53:36,480
There we go.

1140
00:53:40,884 --> 00:53:42,019
[Hesitant]

1141
00:53:47,524 --> 00:53:48,759
[He Pipes On The Tray]

1142
00:53:48,759 --> 00:53:51,361
[And Not On The Bread?]

1143
00:53:53,363 --> 00:53:55,899
[He's Fussing Around]

1144
00:53:55,899 --> 00:54:00,270
[But Unable To Start For Some Reason]

1145
00:54:02,606 --> 00:54:05,275
[The Story Behind]

1146
00:54:05,275 --> 00:54:08,078
[The Paris-Brest's Signature Teardrop Cream]

1147
00:54:08,078 --> 00:54:09,346
Why don't you give it a go?

1148
00:54:09,346 --> 00:54:12,249
[Not Long Ago, In Seoul]

1149
00:54:14,084 --> 00:54:16,353
[Practicing The Teardrop Cream Piping]

1150
00:54:19,990 --> 00:54:20,891
[Topples Over]

1151
00:54:20,891 --> 00:54:22,192
Place it closer...

1152
00:54:22,192 --> 00:54:24,561
Yes, just like that.

1153
00:54:24,561 --> 00:54:26,530
[Squeeze]

1154
00:54:26,530 --> 00:54:27,931
Jeez.

1155
00:54:29,900 --> 00:54:31,969
I can't do this.

1156
00:54:31,969 --> 00:54:34,805
[Then He Tries Again]

1157
00:54:35,539 --> 00:54:39,543
[The Technique That Made
The Legendary King Of Baking Nervous]

1158
00:54:41,311 --> 00:54:45,382
[The Moment Of Truth Has Arrived]

1159
00:55:01,598 --> 00:55:02,766
Okay.

1160
00:55:02,766 --> 00:55:04,935
Okay, it's great.

1161
00:55:13,110 --> 00:55:16,113
[6 Teardrops Complete]

1162
00:55:31,361 --> 00:55:37,267
[Make Small Indents In The Cream
And Fill Them With The Pecan Praline]

1163
00:55:37,267 --> 00:55:39,503
It's getting everywhere.

1164
00:55:41,738 --> 00:55:42,973
Oh, no.

1165
00:55:42,973 --> 00:55:45,843
[It Spread Outside The Teardrop]

1166
00:55:45,843 --> 00:55:49,546
Let me operate on this mess.

1167
00:55:49,546 --> 00:55:51,582
[Begin Surgery]

1168
00:55:51,582 --> 00:55:53,383
[Slight Spill]

1169
00:55:55,152 --> 00:55:57,254
[Hide It With A Pecan]

1170
00:56:04,161 --> 00:56:07,898
One, two, and three.

1171
00:56:07,898 --> 00:56:10,634
[Add 3 Pecans On Top]

1172
00:56:14,304 --> 00:56:15,439
Okay.

1173
00:56:15,439 --> 00:56:16,740
[Finishes Off With Gold Foil]

1174
00:56:25,449 --> 00:56:29,085
[Bonjour Pecan Paris-Brest]

1175
00:56:29,920 --> 00:56:31,021
[Once The Process Is Over]

1176
00:56:31,021 --> 00:56:33,256
<i>This is to refill our energy.</i>

1177
00:56:38,996 --> 00:56:41,465
[Pleased]

1178
00:56:41,465 --> 00:56:43,967
It has a chewy texture.

1179
00:56:43,967 --> 00:56:44,902
- Right?
- Yes.

1180
00:56:44,902 --> 00:56:48,171
It's chewy and delicious like a dessert.

1181
00:56:48,171 --> 00:56:49,306
Yeah, it's chewy.

1182
00:56:49,306 --> 00:56:51,275
[Energy Refilled]
Yes.

1183
00:56:51,275 --> 00:56:53,076
It's good.

1184
00:56:58,148 --> 00:56:59,716
[A Strange Presence]

1185
00:56:59,716 --> 00:57:03,520
[Approaches Hee Ae As She Rings The Bell]

1186
00:57:07,357 --> 00:57:12,129
[They're Actually The Same Group]

1187
00:57:12,129 --> 00:57:16,433
[The Most Peaceful Open Run In The World]

1188
00:57:17,601 --> 00:57:20,704
- You're open again.
- Are you coming here?

1189
00:57:20,704 --> 00:57:22,639
- Hello.
- Hello, ma'am.

1190
00:57:22,639 --> 00:57:23,607
You came yesterday, right?

1191
00:57:23,607 --> 00:57:25,309
- The day before.
- Was it the day before?

1192
00:57:25,309 --> 00:57:27,277
Welcome back.

1193
00:57:27,277 --> 00:57:28,512
[Welcome]
Let's go buy some.

1194
00:57:28,512 --> 00:57:30,247
- Let's go in.
- Hello.

1195
00:57:30,247 --> 00:57:32,049
- Hello.
- How many people?

1196
00:57:32,049 --> 00:57:33,183
- Four people?
- Five.

1197
00:57:33,183 --> 00:57:35,285
Five. Take a seat over there, please.

1198
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:36,553
- Can I check your ID?
- It's fine.

1199
00:57:36,553 --> 00:57:38,422
- They've been here before.
- We were.

1200
00:57:38,422 --> 00:57:39,889
[Customers Who Were Here Before?]

1201
00:57:40,524 --> 00:57:43,794
[Visited With Friends On Opening Day]

1202
00:57:43,794 --> 00:57:44,928
Is it sweet?

1203
00:57:44,928 --> 00:57:45,829
Is it not sweet?

1204
00:57:45,829 --> 00:57:48,565
[Shook Her Head At The Bitter Americano]
It's bitter.

1205
00:57:53,937 --> 00:57:55,339
[Very Satisfied]

1206
00:57:55,339 --> 00:57:58,475
[With The Sweet Syrup]
Why does she keep bringing us stuff?

1207
00:57:58,475 --> 00:58:00,410
- I already checked it.
- You can come inside.

1208
00:58:00,410 --> 00:58:02,646
- Can I take this bug off your shoulder?
- What?

1209
00:58:02,646 --> 00:58:05,315
- Can I take this bug off your shoulder?
- What?

1210
00:58:05,949 --> 00:58:07,751
- There's a bug on your shoulder.
- Just flick it off.

1211
00:58:07,751 --> 00:58:10,020
[I'll Take It Off Before She Gets Scared]

1212
00:58:10,020 --> 00:58:12,889
- There's a bug on your shoulder.
- Just flick it off.

1213
00:58:12,889 --> 00:58:16,793
- What's with this darn bug?
- It's a moth.

1214
00:58:16,793 --> 00:58:19,563
It was a moth. Right this way.

1215
00:58:19,563 --> 00:58:22,332
[Unfazed]

1216
00:58:22,332 --> 00:58:23,734
I wasn't here on that day.

1217
00:58:23,734 --> 00:58:25,335
- You didn't see me, right?
- No.

1218
00:58:25,335 --> 00:58:27,337
I wasn't here.

1219
00:58:27,337 --> 00:58:29,439
[Doesn't Seem To Care]

1220
00:58:30,974 --> 00:58:34,144
Have you had a little drink?

1221
00:58:34,144 --> 00:58:35,212
[Red Face]
He drank.

1222
00:58:35,212 --> 00:58:38,115
Right? I can tell by your face.

1223
00:58:38,115 --> 00:58:39,950
[Their Friend Joins Them]

1224
00:58:39,950 --> 00:58:42,619
[Also Red Face]
Hello, right this way.

1225
00:58:42,619 --> 00:58:44,888
I'm back.

1226
00:58:46,123 --> 00:58:49,459
My wife is over there, so I'll bring her.

1227
00:58:49,459 --> 00:58:51,962
[As For This Elder]
We should visit together.

1228
00:58:51,962 --> 00:58:53,430
[With The Money He Won]

1229
00:58:53,430 --> 00:58:56,666
[He Promised To Come With His Wife]

1230
00:58:56,666 --> 00:58:57,567
I'm back.

1231
00:58:57,567 --> 00:59:00,971
[You Can Tell He Won Big]

1232
00:59:00,971 --> 00:59:01,972
Hello.

1233
00:59:01,972 --> 00:59:03,907
- Did you see Kim Hee Ae?
- Of course.

1234
00:59:03,907 --> 00:59:05,742
We already said hello.

1235
00:59:05,742 --> 00:59:06,843
- Is that you?
- Yes.

1236
00:59:06,843 --> 00:59:08,378
- Ma'am.
- You've never seen her before?

1237
00:59:08,378 --> 00:59:10,113
It's nice to meet you.

1238
00:59:10,113 --> 00:59:11,782
- Do you...
- You're so beautiful.

1239
00:59:11,782 --> 00:59:13,583
- Do you recognize me?
- Kim Seon Ho.

1240
00:59:15,318 --> 00:59:17,754
- He was on <i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night</i>.
- You're right.

1241
00:59:17,754 --> 00:59:19,322
- Yes.
- You're so pretty.

1242
00:59:19,322 --> 00:59:21,224
[Lost Interest In 3 Seconds]
Thank you.

1243
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:22,893
- What about me?
- What?

1244
00:59:22,893 --> 00:59:24,394
- What about me?
- You're so handsome.

1245
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:26,630
[Souless Reply]

1246
00:59:26,630 --> 00:59:28,432
We want to see Chef Cha.

1247
00:59:28,432 --> 00:59:30,667
- Should I call him over?
- Yes.

1248
00:59:31,435 --> 00:59:33,904
Hello.

1249
00:59:33,904 --> 00:59:38,575
[The Next Customers Enter]
Have a seat here. I'll bring a chair over.

1250
00:59:38,575 --> 00:59:41,044
Here's an extra chair.

1251
00:59:41,044 --> 00:59:42,846
- Thank you.
- No problem.

1252
00:59:44,581 --> 00:59:46,616
Stop fooling around.

1253
00:59:46,616 --> 00:59:48,618
Do we order at the counter?

1254
00:59:48,618 --> 00:59:52,522
[Looking Around]

1255
01:00:02,532 --> 01:00:04,034
Are you ready to order?

1256
01:00:04,034 --> 01:00:06,870
- Yes.
- I'll come to your table.

1257
01:00:06,870 --> 01:00:08,772
Please wait just a moment.

1258
01:00:13,577 --> 01:00:15,145
- She's an actress.
- What?

1259
01:00:15,145 --> 01:00:16,480
An actress!

1260
01:00:16,480 --> 01:00:18,248
Mom.

1261
01:00:18,248 --> 01:00:21,118
- Use your manners.
- She's an actress.

1262
01:00:21,118 --> 01:00:24,287
[Yes, It's Actress Kim Hee Ae]

1263
01:00:24,287 --> 01:00:27,124
Here are some warm towels for your hands.

1264
01:00:27,124 --> 01:00:29,859
- Please take your time.
- Thank you.

1265
01:00:32,662 --> 01:00:33,597
Wipe your hands.

1266
01:00:33,597 --> 01:00:34,931
How old are you?

1267
01:00:34,931 --> 01:00:35,932
How old are you?

1268
01:00:35,932 --> 01:00:37,000
I'm six years old.

1269
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:40,170
Six years old? How adorable.

1270
01:00:40,170 --> 01:00:41,605
So you're his grandmother?

1271
01:00:41,605 --> 01:00:44,641
She's my grandmother, and she's my mother.

1272
01:00:44,641 --> 01:00:46,877
And these are my kids.

1273
01:00:46,877 --> 01:00:49,212
- There are four generations here.
- Yes.

1274
01:00:49,212 --> 01:00:51,314
That's awesome.

1275
01:00:51,314 --> 01:00:52,716
What a happy family.

1276
01:00:52,716 --> 01:00:54,518
Congratulations.

1277
01:00:54,518 --> 01:00:55,852
My goodness.

1278
01:00:56,953 --> 01:00:58,755
Take your time.

1279
01:01:03,093 --> 01:01:07,063
My hand is one knuckle bigger than hers.

1280
01:01:11,234 --> 01:01:13,270
- Her wrist hurts.
- You want to try as well?

1281
01:01:13,270 --> 01:01:16,072
[Ache]

1282
01:01:16,072 --> 01:01:17,841
I can use this hand.

1283
01:01:17,841 --> 01:01:19,509
It's one knuckle.

1284
01:01:19,509 --> 01:01:22,179
No, it's two.

1285
01:01:22,179 --> 01:01:23,513
Why? Your wrist hurts?

1286
01:01:23,513 --> 01:01:25,081
Yeah, my bones.

1287
01:01:25,081 --> 01:01:28,185
- It's one knuckle difference.
- Put a relief patch on it before bed.

1288
01:01:28,185 --> 01:01:30,987
Use flour to make a mix.

1289
01:01:30,987 --> 01:01:34,925
Put them on before going to bed at night.

1290
01:01:34,925 --> 01:01:38,094
[Still Worried About Her Daughter
Even If She's Become A Grandma]

1291
01:01:38,094 --> 01:01:39,930
- Flour?
- Yes.

1292
01:01:39,930 --> 01:01:41,731
Just plain flour.

1293
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:44,367
Excuse me.

1294
01:01:44,367 --> 01:01:47,237
- Hold on.
- I'll just squeeze in here.

1295
01:01:47,237 --> 01:01:49,639
Who ordered the iced Americano?

1296
01:01:49,639 --> 01:01:50,707
Here you go.

1297
01:01:50,707 --> 01:01:52,175
This is the lemon honey tea.

1298
01:01:52,175 --> 01:01:53,109
[2 Americano, 1 Lemon Honey Tea]

1299
01:01:53,109 --> 01:01:55,445
[1 Citron Madeleine, 1 Financier,
1 Babka, 1 Sweet Potato Cake]

1300
01:01:55,445 --> 01:01:58,782
- What's your name?
- I'll pick it up.

1301
01:01:58,782 --> 01:02:00,417
Jang Ro Yun.

1302
01:02:00,417 --> 01:02:01,918
- No Yun?
- Ro Yun.

1303
01:02:01,918 --> 01:02:03,954
Ro Yun.

1304
01:02:03,954 --> 01:02:06,623
It's nice to meet you, Ro Yun.

1305
01:02:06,623 --> 01:02:08,692
It's nice to meet you, Ro Yun.

1306
01:02:08,692 --> 01:02:10,594
How did you pick this up?

1307
01:02:10,594 --> 01:02:12,495
[Shyly Changes The Subject]
I picked it up.

1308
01:02:14,764 --> 01:02:16,399
Let's hop on over there.

1309
01:02:20,670 --> 01:02:22,539
We're going to have bread.

1310
01:02:22,539 --> 01:02:23,540
You like them.

1311
01:02:23,540 --> 01:02:25,942
- I like bread.
- You like bread?

1312
01:02:25,942 --> 01:02:27,310
[A Bread-Lover Visits Bonjour Bakery]

1313
01:02:27,310 --> 01:02:28,511
What's that?

1314
01:02:28,511 --> 01:02:29,846
It's bread.

1315
01:02:29,846 --> 01:02:31,314
- Yes, it's bread.
- It's bread.

1316
01:02:31,314 --> 01:02:32,949
You can get baked goods to go.

1317
01:02:32,949 --> 01:02:35,418
- Hello, are you Mrs. Lee Gwi Rae?
- Yes.

1318
01:02:35,418 --> 01:02:36,486
So...

1319
01:02:36,486 --> 01:02:38,755
Oh, it's the three of you.

1320
01:02:38,755 --> 01:02:40,257
Sorry for calling you Mrs.

1321
01:02:40,257 --> 01:02:43,393
- Her name is Jennie?
- Yes.

1322
01:02:43,393 --> 01:02:45,061
The famous one?

1323
01:02:45,061 --> 01:02:46,696
Please come this way.

1324
01:02:48,431 --> 01:02:50,533
There's a lot of people here.

1325
01:02:50,533 --> 01:02:52,469
We're a popular cafe.

1326
01:02:52,469 --> 01:02:53,370
[Time To Brag]

1327
01:02:53,370 --> 01:02:55,438
Have a seat here.

1328
01:02:56,406 --> 01:02:57,607
- There you go.
- Jennie.

1329
01:02:57,607 --> 01:03:00,043
[Lee Gwi Rae, Lee Jennie, Lee Se Won]

1330
01:03:00,043 --> 01:03:02,412
- Do they have what you like, Jennie?
- What is that?

1331
01:03:02,412 --> 01:03:03,346
"Sweet Potato Cake."

1332
01:03:03,346 --> 01:03:05,615
Do you want Sweet Potato Cake, Jennie?

1333
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:07,217
Should we eat Sweet Potato Cake?

1334
01:03:07,217 --> 01:03:09,185
[Nods]
"Camellia Tart."

1335
01:03:09,185 --> 01:03:11,321
- This one's too sweet.
- Okay.

1336
01:03:11,321 --> 01:03:12,656
This one's too sweet?

1337
01:03:12,656 --> 01:03:15,458
- Yes, it's too sweet for you.
- "Green Barley Madeleine."

1338
01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:16,826
This one's too sweet?

1339
01:03:16,826 --> 01:03:19,896
The madeleine is also too sweet for you.

1340
01:03:19,896 --> 01:03:22,799
- Bokbunja...
- "<i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine."

1341
01:03:22,799 --> 01:03:24,067
One Sweet Potato Cake.

1342
01:03:24,067 --> 01:03:27,971
One Green Barley Madeleine
and one <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine, please.

1343
01:03:27,971 --> 01:03:32,275
- We're out of <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine.
- We'll just have the green barley one.

1344
01:03:32,275 --> 01:03:33,910
And one financier.

1345
01:03:34,577 --> 01:03:36,313
Two cups of chamomile, please.

1346
01:03:36,313 --> 01:03:38,414
- Two cups of chamomile.
- Yes.

1347
01:03:41,251 --> 01:03:44,354
- Can we have one Sweet Potato Cake?
- Okay.

1348
01:03:44,354 --> 01:03:47,624
[I'll Cut A Fresh Slice For You Right Away]

1349
01:04:00,603 --> 01:04:02,572
- Okay.
- Yes.

1350
01:04:04,107 --> 01:04:06,275
[Flustered]

1351
01:04:07,644 --> 01:04:08,911
[Trying To Fix It]

1352
01:04:09,512 --> 01:04:12,816
- I'm sorry.
- Someone spilled coffee.

1353
01:04:12,816 --> 01:04:16,252
We have spilled coffee and the cake.

1354
01:04:16,252 --> 01:04:17,921
A customer spilled the coffee.

1355
01:04:17,921 --> 01:04:19,189
- What?
- Did Ki Taek spill that?

1356
01:04:19,189 --> 01:04:20,523
- I saved it.
- Really?

1357
01:04:20,523 --> 01:04:23,193
- I saved it.
- It was done by a customer on our side.

1358
01:04:23,193 --> 01:04:25,628
[Jeez]

1359
01:04:25,628 --> 01:04:28,131
Thankfully, I saved it.

1360
01:04:28,131 --> 01:04:30,066
Don't make excuses.

1361
01:04:30,066 --> 01:04:31,568
[Laughs Together]

1362
01:04:31,568 --> 01:04:33,703
My heart almost stopped.

1363
01:04:36,039 --> 01:04:38,975
This cutlery is especially for Jennie.

1364
01:04:38,975 --> 01:04:40,577
- All right.
- This is a bib.

1365
01:04:40,577 --> 01:04:42,512
Doesn't it look delicious, Jennie?

1366
01:04:42,512 --> 01:04:43,813
Enjoy.

1367
01:04:45,448 --> 01:04:46,850
Okay, I'll give you some.

1368
01:04:46,850 --> 01:04:48,651
Let's put this on first.

1369
01:04:48,651 --> 01:04:50,653
- I want this one.
- This one?

1370
01:04:50,653 --> 01:04:52,355
Okay, I'll cut it for you.

1371
01:04:52,355 --> 01:04:53,857
[Jennie Picks The Financier]

1372
01:04:53,857 --> 01:04:55,258
- Try the financier.
- Here.

1373
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:57,894
[Takes A Bite]

1374
01:04:57,894 --> 01:05:02,298
[It's Yummy]

1375
01:05:05,335 --> 01:05:06,469
Is it good?

1376
01:05:06,469 --> 01:05:08,872
It's so, so yummy.

1377
01:05:08,872 --> 01:05:11,307
Is it yummy?

1378
01:05:12,642 --> 01:05:17,013
[4:19 P.M.]

1379
01:05:20,750 --> 01:05:21,985
Ma'am!

1380
01:05:21,985 --> 01:05:24,454
You should come. Where are you going instead?

1381
01:05:24,454 --> 01:05:25,455
I already stopped by.

1382
01:05:25,455 --> 01:05:26,723
That's true.

1383
01:05:26,723 --> 01:05:28,057
[Just Wanted To Talk To You]
Where are you headed?

1384
01:05:28,057 --> 01:05:30,226
I'm bringing this over there.

1385
01:05:30,226 --> 01:05:32,061
- Where?
- The village head's house.

1386
01:05:32,061 --> 01:05:33,563
Oh, I see.

1387
01:05:33,563 --> 01:05:36,800
Please tell him to stop by.

1388
01:05:36,800 --> 01:05:38,435
[Promoting The Bakery]

1389
01:05:38,435 --> 01:05:41,337
- Have a nice day!
- Thanks.

1390
01:05:43,606 --> 01:05:45,308
[Who Is He Talking To?]
I'm in a good mood.

1391
01:05:45,308 --> 01:05:47,977
- Here are some warm towels.
- Thank you.

1392
01:05:47,977 --> 01:05:49,846
- I'm a fan.
- Thank you.

1393
01:05:49,846 --> 01:05:51,815
You're so beautiful.

1394
01:05:51,815 --> 01:05:54,951
- Please take your time with the menu.
- Okay.

1395
01:05:56,186 --> 01:05:57,454
[Their Eyes Stray Somewhere Else]

1396
01:05:57,454 --> 01:05:58,455
Oh, my.

1397
01:05:58,455 --> 01:05:59,989
[Chuckling]

1398
01:05:59,989 --> 01:06:03,259
Look!

1399
01:06:03,259 --> 01:06:04,961
What's this?

1400
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:06,463
Look behind you.

1401
01:06:06,463 --> 01:06:08,965
It's our in-laws.

1402
01:06:08,965 --> 01:06:10,033
Honey.

1403
01:06:10,033 --> 01:06:13,069
[The View Got Blocked Just In Time]
Our in-laws are behind you.

1404
01:06:13,069 --> 01:06:14,337
Se Won's family is over there.

1405
01:06:14,337 --> 01:06:15,805
- Really?
- Yes.

1406
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:19,309
[As Calm As If Nothing's Happening]
Look, it's Jennie's grandfather.

1407
01:06:19,309 --> 01:06:22,078
He's smiling at Jennie.

1408
01:06:22,078 --> 01:06:24,481
He's looking at her so sweetly.

1409
01:06:24,481 --> 01:06:25,882
[The In-Law Looking At Her So Sweetly]

1410
01:06:25,882 --> 01:06:28,451
- Look at him. He adores her.
- Are you pouring me some tea?

1411
01:06:28,451 --> 01:06:30,854
[Jennie's Grandparents On Her Mom's Side]

1412
01:06:30,854 --> 01:06:32,689
- No.
- What?

1413
01:06:32,689 --> 01:06:34,958
That's Grandma.

1414
01:06:34,958 --> 01:06:36,493
Your grandma's behind you, Jennie.

1415
01:06:36,493 --> 01:06:38,861
- Where?
- Wait a minute.

1416
01:06:39,629 --> 01:06:42,131
Look, Jennie. Grandma's here.

1417
01:06:42,131 --> 01:06:43,900
It's Grandma.

1418
01:06:43,900 --> 01:06:46,469
It's Grandma!

1419
01:06:46,469 --> 01:06:47,971
- Are you guys family?
- Yes.

1420
01:06:47,971 --> 01:06:50,206
- They're my in-laws.
- I see.

1421
01:06:50,206 --> 01:06:52,575
Hey, Jennie. You're here.

1422
01:06:52,575 --> 01:06:54,777
What a coincidence.

1423
01:06:54,777 --> 01:06:56,813
I had no idea you were here.

1424
01:06:56,813 --> 01:06:58,081
What a coincidence.

1425
01:06:58,081 --> 01:07:00,950
Don't go!

1426
01:07:00,950 --> 01:07:02,585
- Jennie.
- We didn't even plan it.

1427
01:07:02,585 --> 01:07:04,754
[Silent Sweetness Overload]
We ran into each other here.

1428
01:07:04,754 --> 01:07:08,391
They ran into each other here.

1429
01:07:13,696 --> 01:07:17,366
[These Financiers Stop Anyone
In Their Tracks]

1430
01:07:18,334 --> 01:07:21,037
Everything's sold out.

1431
01:07:21,037 --> 01:07:22,639
- One of this.
- One citron?

1432
01:07:22,639 --> 01:07:23,640
- Yes.
- Okay.

1433
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:25,208
One green barley.

1434
01:07:25,208 --> 01:07:27,577
- One Green Barley Madeleine.
- Yes.

1435
01:07:27,577 --> 01:07:28,845
- One coffee.
- Yes.

1436
01:07:28,845 --> 01:07:30,580
- Hot americano?
- Yes.

1437
01:07:30,580 --> 01:07:32,549
[Helping Hee Ae Handle Customers Calmly]
Yes, two cups.

1438
01:07:32,549 --> 01:07:35,184
[Assist With Taking Orders]
Two hot americano.

1439
01:07:35,184 --> 01:07:36,553
[To Help Hee Ae]
What would you like to order to go?

1440
01:07:36,553 --> 01:07:39,222
- I'll take two of each, please.
- Okay.

1441
01:07:39,222 --> 01:07:40,123
This is sold out.

1442
01:07:40,123 --> 01:07:41,591
- Citron.
- Yes.

1443
01:07:41,591 --> 01:07:42,492
[These Are For Here]

1444
01:07:42,492 --> 01:07:44,527
- Madeleine.
- Two green barley.

1445
01:07:44,527 --> 01:07:47,297
- Two Green Barley Madeleines to go.
- Yes, please.

1446
01:07:47,297 --> 01:07:49,432
And two Chestnut Pumpkin Babka.

1447
01:07:49,432 --> 01:07:50,700
Babka.

1448
01:07:50,700 --> 01:07:52,235
One financier.

1449
01:07:52,235 --> 01:07:53,703
Financier.

1450
01:07:54,404 --> 01:07:57,840
- Do you want to take it on your way out?
- Yes.

1451
01:07:58,575 --> 01:08:00,376
- I'll pay for it.
- You can insert your card.

1452
01:08:00,376 --> 01:08:02,278
- I'll pay for it.
- It's okay.

1453
01:08:02,278 --> 01:08:03,913
- I'll pay for it.
- You can insert your card.

1454
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:05,515
- I'll pay for it.
- It's okay.

1455
01:08:05,515 --> 01:08:07,517
[All They Need To Do Is Pay]
They're my in-laws, so...

1456
01:08:07,517 --> 01:08:09,118
They're my in-laws, so...

1457
01:08:09,118 --> 01:08:10,954
- I'll pay for everything.
- Okay.

1458
01:08:10,954 --> 01:08:12,722
[After Some Argument]
I'll pay for everything later.

1459
01:08:12,722 --> 01:08:15,324
[The In-Laws Will Be Paying]
All right.

1460
01:08:16,726 --> 01:08:17,794
I got it.

1461
01:08:17,794 --> 01:08:20,196
- I'll pay for it all together.
- Okay.

1462
01:08:21,164 --> 01:08:22,732
- You're paying for it?
- Yes.

1463
01:08:22,732 --> 01:08:24,367
[In Awe]

1464
01:08:24,367 --> 01:08:27,503
Sir, could you...

1465
01:08:27,503 --> 01:08:30,406
Sir, could you give me your card?

1466
01:08:30,406 --> 01:08:32,175
I'm sorry, but...

1467
01:08:32,175 --> 01:08:33,943
- Can you pay first?
- I'm...

1468
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:35,745
- I'm a bit slow.
- Okay.

1469
01:08:35,745 --> 01:08:37,981
I was about to ring it up.

1470
01:08:37,981 --> 01:08:40,283
It takes a while to start over.

1471
01:08:41,117 --> 01:08:43,486
Thank you very much.

1472
01:08:43,486 --> 01:08:45,655
We should've come together.

1473
01:08:45,655 --> 01:08:47,190
I know, right?

1474
01:08:47,190 --> 01:08:48,791
[1 Citron Madeleine,
1 Green Barley Madeleine]

1475
01:08:48,791 --> 01:08:50,560
They are so pretty.

1476
01:08:50,560 --> 01:08:53,362
<i>The green barley color is so pretty.</i>

1477
01:08:56,466 --> 01:08:58,167
You should try this one.

1478
01:09:01,571 --> 01:09:03,339
It's good.

1479
01:09:03,339 --> 01:09:05,441
I can smell the barley.

1480
01:09:06,342 --> 01:09:08,044
It tastes fresh.

1481
01:09:09,078 --> 01:09:11,681
- It tastes unique.
- Yes, it's delicious.

1482
01:09:11,681 --> 01:09:13,416
Is this citron?

1483
01:09:13,416 --> 01:09:15,485
Have you lived here long?

1484
01:09:15,485 --> 01:09:17,053
It's only been around 7 or 8 months.

1485
01:09:17,053 --> 01:09:18,287
- Seven or eight months?
- Yes.

1486
01:09:18,287 --> 01:09:20,189
Where did you live before?

1487
01:09:20,790 --> 01:09:22,759
We used to live in Mokpo, Jeonnam.

1488
01:09:22,759 --> 01:09:24,894
How did you end up here?

1489
01:09:24,894 --> 01:09:29,132
We came to help raise
our beautiful granddaughter.

1490
01:09:29,132 --> 01:09:31,434
- Jennie?
- Yes.

1491
01:09:31,434 --> 01:09:32,869
Do you live here now for good?

1492
01:09:32,869 --> 01:09:33,936
- Yes.
- Yes.

1493
01:09:33,936 --> 01:09:36,505
- You moved closer to your daughter.
- Yes.

1494
01:09:37,340 --> 01:09:38,841
It must be nice, right?

1495
01:09:38,841 --> 01:09:41,044
Yes, it's really nice.

1496
01:09:41,044 --> 01:09:43,780
And we love Gochang.

1497
01:09:43,780 --> 01:09:47,216
[I Love Madeleines]

1498
01:09:47,216 --> 01:09:51,954
- The baked goods from the in-laws.
- Right.

1499
01:09:51,954 --> 01:09:54,056
Come again. Thank you.

1500
01:09:55,825 --> 01:09:57,427
Here's the Pecan Paris-Brest

1501
01:09:57,427 --> 01:09:59,929
and Sweet Potato Cake.

1502
01:09:59,929 --> 01:10:02,264
Hello.

1503
01:10:02,899 --> 01:10:06,202
Thanks to my daughter,
I'm trying all sorts of things.

1504
01:10:06,202 --> 01:10:09,772
You weren't supposed to come today.

1505
01:10:09,772 --> 01:10:11,708
- I was supposed to get off work alone.
- Yes.

1506
01:10:11,708 --> 01:10:13,843
But I wanted to come, too.

1507
01:10:13,843 --> 01:10:17,480
I could only come because of you.

1508
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:19,182
- That's true.
- Yes.

1509
01:10:19,182 --> 01:10:22,485
Our roles are reversed for once.

1510
01:10:23,252 --> 01:10:25,121
- Mr. Lee Geon Oh?
- Yes, hello.

1511
01:10:25,121 --> 01:10:27,256
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

1512
01:10:27,256 --> 01:10:29,625
Nice to meet you. Welcome.

1513
01:10:30,259 --> 01:10:31,728
Sir.

1514
01:10:31,728 --> 01:10:36,232
I'll have to ask you for your ID.

1515
01:10:36,232 --> 01:10:38,167
- Thank you.
- You look so young.

1516
01:10:38,167 --> 01:10:40,470
[Happy To Show His ID]
It's hard to tell.

1517
01:10:40,470 --> 01:10:42,205
Let me see.

1518
01:10:42,205 --> 01:10:43,339
You look young for your age.

1519
01:10:43,339 --> 01:10:44,874
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1520
01:10:44,874 --> 01:10:48,044
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1521
01:10:48,044 --> 01:10:49,579
[Hold On]

1522
01:10:49,579 --> 01:10:52,748
[I Want To Show Off My Daughter]

1523
01:10:53,349 --> 01:10:58,221
I'm glad we managed to stop by
on the last day.

1524
01:10:58,221 --> 01:10:59,522
- Really?
- I'm honored.

1525
01:10:59,522 --> 01:11:01,491
- You happened to stop by?
- You see.

1526
01:11:01,491 --> 01:11:04,727
My daughter was first assigned

1527
01:11:04,727 --> 01:11:07,830
to Gapyeong Elementary School here.

1528
01:11:07,830 --> 01:11:08,998
You're a teacher?

1529
01:11:08,998 --> 01:11:12,935
I'm here for counseling
at Gapyeong Elementary School.

1530
01:11:12,935 --> 01:11:14,170
Really?

1531
01:11:15,538 --> 01:11:18,341
You must be so proud of your daughter.

1532
01:11:18,341 --> 01:11:19,242
Yes.

1533
01:11:19,242 --> 01:11:20,409
[Happy]

1534
01:11:21,244 --> 01:11:25,014
[Happy That The Bakery Happens
To Be In Front Of The School]

1535
01:11:25,014 --> 01:11:26,149
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

1536
01:11:26,149 --> 01:11:28,784
[Sweet Potato Cake]
Let me bring another fork.

1537
01:11:29,385 --> 01:11:30,886
Should we try it?

1538
01:11:42,131 --> 01:11:43,566
How is it?

1539
01:11:43,566 --> 01:11:44,967
It's delicious.

1540
01:11:46,602 --> 01:11:50,439
- He must've made it himself, right?
- It's very soft.

1541
01:11:56,078 --> 01:11:59,282
Do you need two months
before you can drive home by yourself?

1542
01:11:59,282 --> 01:12:01,517
It's hard to come on your own, right?

1543
01:12:02,151 --> 01:12:04,720
[Just Got Her License]
I'm not sure.

1544
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:06,022
I'm still thinking.

1545
01:12:06,022 --> 01:12:09,492
It's easy to get to the terminal
from the main street.

1546
01:12:09,492 --> 01:12:11,660
Don't go to the narrow streets.

1547
01:12:19,001 --> 01:12:21,537
Thanks for doing that yourself.

1548
01:12:21,537 --> 01:12:25,074
Hee Ae didn't seem to want to do it.

1549
01:12:26,309 --> 01:12:29,312
You're such a rascal.

1550
01:12:29,312 --> 01:12:30,947
We don't need to refill the case, do we?

1551
01:12:30,947 --> 01:12:32,715
No, I don't think so.

1552
01:12:32,715 --> 01:12:34,784
Can you make one iced Americano?

1553
01:12:34,784 --> 01:12:36,385
- Sounds great.
- For...

1554
01:12:36,385 --> 01:12:38,054
- Everyone should have a glass of decaf.
- He's really good.

1555
01:12:38,054 --> 01:12:38,955
He's really good.

1556
01:12:38,955 --> 01:12:40,122
[Ki Taek Is Really Good]

1557
01:12:41,891 --> 01:12:44,260
[Ki Taek Hums Happily]

1558
01:12:44,260 --> 01:12:47,396
- I only want a quarter of that.
- Okay.

1559
01:12:48,531 --> 01:12:50,099
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1560
01:12:50,099 --> 01:12:52,368
You're so thoughtful.

1561
01:12:56,305 --> 01:12:57,907
How's the Sweet Potato Cake?

1562
01:12:57,907 --> 01:12:59,742
- It's good.
- It's very good.

1563
01:12:59,742 --> 01:13:03,379
Right? I've never seen anything like this.

1564
01:13:03,379 --> 01:13:07,316
It's made from Gochang sweet potatoes,
which makes it extra good.

1565
01:13:07,316 --> 01:13:10,186
- It's the best one I've ever tried.
- I agree.

1566
01:13:10,186 --> 01:13:13,556
[Listening Carefully]
It's fresh and not too sweet.

1567
01:13:13,556 --> 01:13:16,192
How did you two come here together?

1568
01:13:16,192 --> 01:13:20,997
I drove for the first time
while going to work.

1569
01:13:20,997 --> 01:13:23,532
My dad was worried about me.

1570
01:13:23,532 --> 01:13:26,736
So he commutes with me.

1571
01:13:26,736 --> 01:13:29,305
- He's been training me.
- I'm teaching her.

1572
01:13:29,305 --> 01:13:30,706
From the beginning.

1573
01:13:30,706 --> 01:13:32,708
How will she ever get married?

1574
01:13:32,708 --> 01:13:33,676
I didn't cry

1575
01:13:33,676 --> 01:13:36,746
when my elder daughter got married.

1576
01:13:36,746 --> 01:13:38,047
[He Didn't Say He Wouldn't Cry]
You have two daughters?

1577
01:13:38,047 --> 01:13:40,082
[When Sending Off The Youngest One]
No, I have one son in the middle.

1578
01:13:40,082 --> 01:13:43,319
- You won't cry, will you?
- I won't.

1579
01:13:47,256 --> 01:13:50,326
I can tell what a good person you are.

1580
01:13:50,326 --> 01:13:53,496
Are you training someone here?

1581
01:13:53,496 --> 01:13:55,831
- I'm a counselor.
- Counselor.

1582
01:13:55,831 --> 01:13:58,067
People go to the nurse
to heal their bodies, right?

1583
01:13:58,067 --> 01:14:00,670
People come to me to heal their minds.

1584
01:14:00,670 --> 01:14:05,041
Really? You're doing something great.

1585
01:14:05,041 --> 01:14:09,078
You should bring this to your mother.

1586
01:14:09,078 --> 01:14:11,080
Since she couldn't come.

1587
01:14:11,080 --> 01:14:12,815
It's nothing big, but take it.

1588
01:14:12,815 --> 01:14:14,083
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1589
01:14:14,083 --> 01:14:16,652
My wife is waiting for us back home.

1590
01:14:16,652 --> 01:14:17,653
Of course.

1591
01:14:17,653 --> 01:14:21,290
- She'll be happy if you bring her a gift.
- Yes.

1592
01:14:21,290 --> 01:14:22,291
<i>Take care.</i>

1593
01:14:22,291 --> 01:14:24,426
<i>- Thank you.</i>
<i>- Thank you.</i>

1594
01:14:26,929 --> 01:14:31,667
He's been riding with me since Monday.

1595
01:14:31,667 --> 01:14:32,835
We would head to work together,

1596
01:14:32,835 --> 01:14:35,371
and then he would drive back home.

1597
01:14:35,371 --> 01:14:37,773
Then he'd come back when I got off work.

1598
01:14:37,773 --> 01:14:43,012
Even in high school,
he used to go to and from school with me.

1599
01:14:43,012 --> 01:14:47,716
I'm thankful for his love.

1600
01:14:52,355 --> 01:14:57,093
How do you feel now
that your youngest daughter is grown?

1601
01:14:57,093 --> 01:15:02,731
She grew up so fast,
and now she looks out for me.

1602
01:15:03,499 --> 01:15:06,468
It's rewarding to see her grow.

1603
01:15:07,603 --> 01:15:11,941
I'll try to give back the love my parents
gave me to my students.

1604
01:15:11,941 --> 01:15:15,344
[Beginner Driver]

1605
01:15:17,680 --> 01:15:20,582
- Drive safely.
- Thank you.

1606
01:15:35,601 --> 01:15:36,920
[Bonjour Bakery]

1607
01:15:41,470 --> 01:15:42,471
You know...

1608
01:15:42,471 --> 01:15:43,539
Is there Camellia Tart?

1609
01:15:43,539 --> 01:15:45,374
Yes, have some. Come here.

1610
01:15:45,374 --> 01:15:48,511
- I'm getting a Camellia Tart for him.
- Seon Ho.

1611
01:15:48,511 --> 01:15:49,979
It looks delicious.

1612
01:15:49,979 --> 01:15:51,447
Do you want some?

1613
01:15:51,447 --> 01:15:53,015
Let's split one in thirds and share it.

1614
01:15:53,015 --> 01:15:54,450
No, don't do that.

1615
01:15:54,450 --> 01:15:55,351
Just have one.

1616
01:15:55,351 --> 01:15:57,353
No, it's okay.

1617
01:15:57,353 --> 01:15:59,155
- Why?
- It's such a waste.

1618
01:15:59,155 --> 01:16:00,756
What do you mean?

1619
01:16:00,756 --> 01:16:02,425
You worked so hard for it.

1620
01:16:02,425 --> 01:16:03,826
- I'm going.
- Okay.

1621
01:16:03,826 --> 01:16:05,227
[Run Before Guilt Kicks In]
I'll eat it with Hee Ae.

1622
01:16:05,227 --> 01:16:06,795
Is that for us?

1623
01:16:07,930 --> 01:16:10,099
I wanted to try some, so I asked.

1624
01:16:10,099 --> 01:16:12,668
- Who did you ask?
- I asked Seung Won confidently.

1625
01:16:12,668 --> 01:16:15,271
Confidently? You're so cute.

1626
01:16:15,271 --> 01:16:16,539
- When...
- I don't feel bad.

1627
01:16:16,539 --> 01:16:17,973
Since when do you feel bad?

1628
01:16:17,973 --> 01:16:19,875
- One piece each?
- Yes.

1629
01:16:20,709 --> 01:16:23,679
- I'll go first.
- Yes, go ahead.

1630
01:16:26,682 --> 01:16:28,784
Is it good? Is that why you're frowning?

1631
01:16:28,784 --> 01:16:30,819
I had too much for lunch.

1632
01:16:36,792 --> 01:16:38,661
Isn't it great?

1633
01:16:38,661 --> 01:16:41,063
[Look At You, Camellia Tart]
Doesn't it just make you happy?

1634
01:16:41,063 --> 01:16:43,966
How is it the right amount of sweetness?

1635
01:16:46,302 --> 01:16:47,936
This is so good.

1636
01:16:48,671 --> 01:16:50,339
- Did you try the Camellia Tart?
- What?

1637
01:16:50,339 --> 01:16:51,474
- The Camellia Tart.
- Yes.

1638
01:16:51,474 --> 01:16:53,342
- How is it?
- It's really good.

1639
01:16:53,342 --> 01:16:55,678
- Hee Ae...
- Hee Ae closed her eyes.

1640
01:16:55,678 --> 01:16:57,146
It's so delicious.

1641
01:16:57,146 --> 01:16:58,614
Is there anything else to eat?

1642
01:16:58,614 --> 01:17:00,349
Another one? What do you want?

1643
01:17:00,349 --> 01:17:03,185
I haven't tried the Crème Brûlée.

1644
01:17:06,989 --> 01:17:08,824
- Tap, tap, tap.
- Yes.

1645
01:17:08,824 --> 01:17:11,861
As expected, you know how to eat it.

1646
01:17:11,861 --> 01:17:13,262
- Just like this.
- Try it.

1647
01:17:13,262 --> 01:17:15,464
I just torched it.

1648
01:17:15,464 --> 01:17:16,765
Just now.

1649
01:17:20,169 --> 01:17:22,438
This is amazing. You could sell it in Paris.

1650
01:17:22,438 --> 01:17:24,139
- This?
- Yes.

1651
01:17:24,807 --> 01:17:26,008
It's good, right?

1652
01:17:26,008 --> 01:17:28,177
[I, Kim Hee Ae, Realized Something]
I love this one.

1653
01:17:28,177 --> 01:17:29,912
[There's Always Room For Dessert]
It's amazing, right?

1654
01:17:29,912 --> 01:17:31,480
Have you tried it?

1655
01:17:31,480 --> 01:17:34,616
I've been eating too much lately.

1656
01:17:37,853 --> 01:17:39,955
I'm going to gain at least 2kg.

1657
01:17:39,955 --> 01:17:42,758
I think I've eaten one year's amount.

1658
01:17:42,758 --> 01:17:44,426
One year's amount.

1659
01:17:44,426 --> 01:17:45,928
When else will I get the chance?

1660
01:17:45,928 --> 01:17:47,997
This is what life's about.

1661
01:17:47,997 --> 01:17:49,265
That's how it is.
